title: irish coffee
directions: Pour Irish whiskey into Irish coffee mug.
Drop in one lump of sugar.
Fill with strong, hot black coffee.
Stir.
Pour whipped cream off back of a teaspoon, so cream stays on top of coffee. Sip coffee through cream.

title: ruby tuesday's pink lemonade
directions: Mix together well.
Serve in tall glass over ice.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot. Cover with water and cook until meat and vegetables are falling apart. Taste and add seasonings if needed.

title: barley casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add barley and brown. Add crushed garlic clove.
Pour into greased casserole.
Pour over this 1 cup of chicken broth.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover.
Add second cup of chicken broth.
Stir.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake until liquid is absorbed (approximately 1/2 hour).

title: italian dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix seasoning with cream cheese and Parmesan cheese and spread over bottom of pie plate.
Toss on 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese; spread on sauce and top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with bread sticks.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and shred.
Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Fold in sour cream last.
Pour into buttered or sprayed casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and sugar.
Add vegetable oil, molasses, eggs and rolled oats.
Mix until blended.
Stir in raisins.
Dough will be soft.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoons onto nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350 for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 1 minute.
Remove from baking sheet and cool. Yield: 48 cookies.

title: pineapple pecan loaf
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice to creamed mixture; stir well after each addition.
Stir in undrained pineapple and nuts.
Turn into well-greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: no name appetizer
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread on English muffin halves.
Cut halves into 4 wedges.
Place under broiler until bubbly.
Serve warm.
Great and simple!

title: peter paul cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to margarine mixture.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix corn meal with flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and milk; blend in oil.
Mix well.
Dip wieners in batter. Fry in deep fat.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and gelatin into 8 x 11-inch baking dish. Spread dry cake mix over rhubarb.
Pour water over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pineappleade
directions: Combine juice and lemonade concentrate.
Just before serving, add carbonated beverage.
Serve over ice in tall glasses.
Garnish with lemon slices and cherries.
Serves 9 (8 ounce) servings.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, mix together sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Heat in microwave on High until boils.
Boil for 5 minutes. Stir. Boil again on High for 8 to 12 minutes or hard ball stage. Remove from microwave and cool.

title: pat's sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, pudding mix, milk, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in a small mixer bowl.
Beat at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 20 minutes before serving. Garnish with additional topping, if desired.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Melt butter and add sugar and flour.
Mix well and add nuts. Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes or until cool enough to roll into small balls, about the size of a walnut.
Cook at 300° until golden brown (20 minutes or more).
Remove and roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Roll again when cool.

title: oatmeal batter bread
directions: Mix the salt, yeast and 2 cups flour in a large bowl.
Combine the oatmeal, light molasses, water and margarine in a saucepan; heat to 120° to 130°.
In mixer, add liquids to dry.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes by hand.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups flour.
Cover bowl (no knead).
Rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Grease 2 (2-quart) casserole bowls; divide dough. Turn to grease top.
Rise until double (30 to 45 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Brush melted margarine on top when done.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients well on beater for 5 minutes.
Pour half the batter in the prepared pan.
Prepare topping of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour half the topping on batter in pan.
Swirl with a fork.
Pour in the rest of the batter.
Sprinkle on the rest of the topping.
Swirl with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 65 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix seasonings; sprinkle over bread cubes.
Add onion mixture and water.
Combine. Stuff thawed, rinsed turkey and roast immediately.
Yield:
4 cups (enough for 6 pound turkey).

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Peel eggs and separate yolk from white.
Dice egg whites.
Next add egg yolks to mayonnaise and mix.
Grate onion into mix.
Add white wine vinegar and celery seeds.
Mix, chill and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti 1
directions: Cook spaghetti in broth of cooked chicken, with water added to make enough liquid.
While this is cooking, fry onion in oil until clear.
Add pepper and tomato soup.
Add mushrooms and simmer. Chop cooked chicken and place with spaghetti in a large pan.
Add the tomato mixture, cover with grated cheese and place in a slow oven until cheese melts.

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Spray a 6 x 10-inch glass baking dish with cooking oil.
Line a glass dish bottom with crescent dinner rolls.
Cut sausage in half longways on top of rolls; grate cheese and sprinkle on top of sausage.
Beat eggs or Egg Beaters well.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Beat again until double.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove the dish from oven.
Shake to see if egg mixture is set.
Eat while hot.
Mushrooms or chopped vegetables can be added, if wanted.

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Beat eggs.
Add crushed crackers and other ingredients.
Mix well; let stand until mixture raises a little.
Drop by heaping teaspoon to form a pattie, into a heated skillet with a little oil or Crisco, melted.
Brown on each side.
These patties fry fairly fast.

title: easy frosting
directions: Cook to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Beat until thick.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter, add flour and stir to blend.
Add cold milk slowly.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cheese melts.
Serve hot over vegetables.

title: gold angel cake
directions: Beat egg yolks light; add water and beat.
Add sugar and beat. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and stir into egg yolk mixture; add vanilla.

title: butter rolls
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Add flour. Form in rolls.
Roll in colored sugars and slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake about 10 minutes at 370°.
Don't brown.
Very pretty and delicious around the holidays.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix oil and all ingredients.
together.
Put crackers in large sealable container.
Pour mixture over crackers and seal.
Shake well to cover crackers.
Allow to sit for 24 hours (shaking occasionally) before serving.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, sour cream and approximately 1/3 of Cool Whip.
Alternate layers beginning with wafers, bananas, then pudding.
(I usually do about 3 layers.)
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Chill for at least several hours before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Add sugar, corn meal and vinegar to the beaten eggs and continue to beat.
Add melted butter to mixture and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Mix with mixer the cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges.
Put into greased tube pan (I spray with Pam).
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Let cake cool.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Blend together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
When cooled, cut in squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Stir well. Press into bottom of pan.
Combine egg and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Pour over crust.
Put granulated sugar and strawberries in bowl and mix.
Put bananas on top of egg mixture. Alternate layers of strawberries and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and cherries.
Sprinkle pecans over top.

title: colleen's cranberry bread
directions: Cook cranberries with water and sugar until berries start to pop.
Add first seven ingredients together.
Add cranberry mixture to this.

title: spinach and crab casserole
directions: Add lemon juice to crab meat. Mix 1 cup cheese with onion, tomato paste, sour cream, salt, pepper, nutmeg and sherry. Pour over crab meat. Add spinach; mix well and turn into baking dish. Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: punch
directions: Chill orange drink, pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Pour orange drink and pineapple juice into punch bowl.
Add sherbet. Pour in ginger ale just before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine pineapple and dry pudding mix. Mix in whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: praline apple crisp
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl; mix well. Add apples, raisins and lemon juice, tossing to mix.
Pour into buttered pie pan.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and save.
Mix drained pineapple with undrained mixed fruit.
In a separate bowl, mix the pineapple juice with pudding mix, Tang and bananas.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: brown sugar drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in milk. Blend flour, soda, salt; stir into mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoons about 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly with finger.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Beat and pour into shell. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup of hot water until completely dissolved. Add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce. Stir. Chill 45 minutes. Stir in the pineapple, celery and nuts. Chill until set and serve. Makes about 1 large Tupperware mold. Place on leaf of lettuce and serve with Cool Whip.

title: betsy's apple deep dish
directions: Add apples to first mixture and toss.
Arrange apples and sugar and spices in 1-1/2 qt. baking dish.
Then mix second mixtures with fingertips until crumbly then toss on top of apples. Bake 400° for 45 minutes.
1/4 c. sliced toasted almonds may be tossed on top about 15 minutes before baking is complete.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together the flour and soda.
Add egg mixture. Pour in greased tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: rhubarb-jello cake
directions: Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until tests done.
Cool and frost with Cool Whip before serving.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage and onion in a small amount of boiling salted water in saucepan for 10 minutes or until wilted; drain well. Layer cabbage mixture, cheese and soup 1/2 at a time in casserole. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ham, black bean and rice salad
directions: Mix beans, onion, celery and garlic salt. Mix rice and bell pepper. Arrange bean mixture, rice mixture and ham on a serving plate. Serve with Snappy Dressing (see below).

title: jello delight
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with all ingredients.
Chill 3 hours.

title: round steak 'n ravioli
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and seasonings.
Coat meat with flour mixture; reserve remaining mixture.
Melt shortening in skillet; stir in reserved flour mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour over meat; cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: pistachio - almond pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 10 inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 - 55 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, remove and cool on rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: pineapple angel food trifle
directions: Combine pudding mixes and milk.
Blend for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add pineapple tidbits, sour cream and 1/2 cup juice. Tear 1/3 of angel food cake and put in trifle bowl.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons juice over cake to moisten.
Pour pudding mixture over angel food cake.
Alternate this cake and pudding mixture.
Add Cool Whip on top just before serving.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend all ingredients together and spread on tortillas.
Roll and wrap in wax paper.
Let set overnight.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes in 3 layers, sprinkling each layer with 1 tablespoon onion, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper to taste and 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Heat milk to scalding.
Pour over the potatoes.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 60 minutes or until tender.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes before serving.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Fold
in
Cool Whip.
Stir in pecans and fruit.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate several hours.
Delicious and so fattening!

title: peggy's fabulous peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add peaches.
Mix sugar, flour and milk real good.
Pour over peaches; do not stir.
Bake at 325° until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: rice quiche
directions: Mix rice, 1 egg and Swiss cheese.
Press into 9-inch pie pan; refrigerate.
Beat 3 eggs, milk, salt, nutmeg, sugar and pepper. Stir in ham and Cheddar cheese.
Could also add chopped onion if you would like.
Pour into crust and bake 15 minutes at 400°. Reduce and bake at 300° about 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting. Serves 4 to 5.

title: condensed pudding(portuguese)
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Heat some sugar until it turns brown.
Put the sugar in a mold and you put the mix inside.
Put the mold on the stove container which should be filled with water; you let it cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature; mix all ingredients together.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Allow 1 day to chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage well.
Melt cheese and mix with Bisquick and sausage.
Make into small balls.
Freeze on a cookie sheet.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size florets.
Run under hot-hot water for 30 seconds.
Pour ice water over immediately (best to use colander to drain well).
Add onions, cheese and bacon to broccoli and toss.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potato wedges, peel side down on a cookie sheet.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.

title: russian tea
directions: Use 2 teaspoons to one cup of boiling water.

title: vegetable meat pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine egg, catsup, salt, onion powder, chili powder and seasoned pepper; stir in cereal to coat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir mixture to break up cereal.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Press gently into
9-inch pie plate, shaping to fit.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients in order.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cup of butter and salt.
Press in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except stuffing and butter).
Add butter to stuffing.
Put 1/2 in bottom of baking dish and the other 1/2 on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Spray 8 1/2 x 11-inch glass or metal pan with Pam or lightly grease.
Place bread in pan.
Melt oleo and pour over bread.

title: texas skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in chili powder, garlic salt, peppers, tomatoes, beans, rice and water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Cover until cheese melts (3 minutes).
Sprinkle chips around edge.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Boil on stove top until very soft. Drain water.
Add 1/2 stick of butter; stir until melted.
Add sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Add parsley and garlic powder to taste.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: throw together casserole
directions: If using hamburger, brown and drain.
Add meat, potatoes, beans and tomatoes in a baking dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in a 350° oven until hot. Top with shredded cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: london broil
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate steak in sauce for 4 hours. Broil steak.
Slice thin diagonally.

title: campers pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in iron skillet over coals.
Drain on paper towels; season with salt.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles and place in skillet, points toward center, to form circle.
Press together, making crust and rim of crust.
Spread 1/2 pizza sauce over dough.
Spoon ground beef over sauce.
Top with mushrooms, olives and bell pepper.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place pan, covered with foil, over medium coals.
Cook 20 or 30 minutes or until crust is lightly brown.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes until tender.
Cook onion in olive oil until light tan in color.
Can be canned at 15 pounds pressure for 1 hour.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and margarine, mixing well.
Mix in the onion and spinach.
Stir in the cheese. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Grease wax paper and line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Set
aside.
Sift
together
flour, spices and salt.
In bowl, beat
eggs	at
high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar to eggs.
Stir
in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold in dry ingredients. Pour
into
prepared
pan.
Top	with
chopped pecans.
Bake at 375°
for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto a towel sprinkled with powdered
sugar.
Remove wax paper.
Roll from small end,
rolling towel as you roll.
Lift to cooling rack. While cooling,
mix powdered
sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla until
smooth. Spread
on	unrolled
cake and reroll. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Slice.

title: super scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Thinly slice onion.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/3 of potatoes in casserole dish.
Place 1/3 of onion on top.

title: chocolate wheat drops
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and cocoa; boil 1 minute.
Pour over oatmeal and coconut.
Quickly scoop with #40 scoop and drop on trays.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute in pan, garlic powder, salt, onion and celery.
Combine all ingredients, except dressing, and put in casserole dish.
Mix dressing with melted butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° until it's bubbly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bring oleo, peanut butter, water and oil to a boil and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased and floured jelly roll pan or a deep cookie sheet (use large pan).
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Using small amount of bacon drippings, fry onion, green pepper and carrot.
Add scrambled eggs to vegetables.
When done, remove from skillet.
Put butter in skillet and fry cooled rice until brown.
Add chopped meat and the vegetable/egg mixture.
Add seasonings and soy sauce.
Remove from heat and add finely chopped green onion, if desired.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: Use hot water to mix jello; then add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining water.
Mix and pour into mold.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and flavorings.
Beat until light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each. Add sifted dry ingredients alternating with sour cream and brandy. Blend well.
Put in greased 3-quart Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.
Store in airtight container.

title: flake candy
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and cream to soft ball stage.
Add rest of ingredients and stir together.
Spread in a buttered pan.
Use a jelly roll pan or 1/2 sheet pan.
Cool and cut.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour.
Chop candy, dates and nuts and dredge in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add coconut and add to batter.
Bake in angel food cake pan at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Combine 1 cup orange juice and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Pour over cake as soon as removed from oven. Let stand overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg, milk and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple and set aside. Mix together buttermilk and vanilla pudding until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip and then add the fruit. When ready to serve, add chopped cookies.

title: tuna fish dip
directions: Cream together tuna fish, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add to taste the Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, curry powder, grated cheese and grated onion.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening
together, then add eggs and molasses.
Mix spices with
flour.
Alternately
add flour and buttermilk.
Chill and roll
out.
Cut
with cookie cutter and place on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes approximately 5 dozen, depending
on
size
of
cookies.
They keep well and can be frozen.

title: bean and pea salad
directions: Combine peas, beans, celery, pimento, onion and green peppers. Heat sugar, wine vinegar, salad oil, paprika and salt to boiling. Cover vegetables with mixture and refrigerate.

title: ready done tomatoes
directions: Cook very slowly for several hours; stir frequently.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, with fork, beat eggs.
Stir in oil, zucchini and lemon peel.
Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spread batter evenly in pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour the baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry mixture alternately with milk.
Mash 1/2 cup blueberries.
Stir with fork.
Add rest of berries.
Sprinkle muffins with sugar before baking.
Grease muffin pans well.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: capital chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and oil in pan.
Brown chicken and put in casserole dish.
In same frying pan, saute mushrooms 5 minutes. Stir in flour.
Add soup, wine and water.
Simmer until thick. Stir in cream, salt, tarragon and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Mix in artichoke hearts, onions and parsley.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan, over moderate heat, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let harden.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water semi-sweet morsels and butterscotch morsels; stir to blend.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill about 5 minutes, until top is firm.
Cut into bars.
Yields 48 (2 x 1-inch) bars.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix granulated sugar with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over apples and mix lightly.
Spread apples; mix lightly.
Spread apples in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with water.
Blend flour, salt, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Mix in butter to make a crumbly mixture.
Spread over apples. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes, or until lightly browned and apples are tender.

title: pea and potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, peas and salt until tender.
Drain and add the cream of mushroom soup, thinned with 1/2 cup milk.
Heat and serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all together and cook until done to taste.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: pasta salad
directions: Wash and dry vegetables.
Slice green onions, carrots, black olives, baby corn, zucchini and yellow squash.
Put all vegetables in large serving bowl.
Add cooked rotini.
Mix 1/3 bottle of Zesty Italian dressing with 1 - 16 oz. jar of mayonnaise and blend in with vegetable mixture.
Chill and serve with fresh grated parmesan cheese.

title: easy sherbet punch
directions: Spoon sherbet by tablespoons into a large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled lemon-lime beverage; stir gently to mix.
Makes 36 (4 ounce) servings.

title: jalapeno pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers or use to stuff celery.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Add 2 more quarts of water and simmer 20 minutes.
Skim off tea bags, cloves and cinnamon.
Serve warm or hot.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Next, put buttered crackers on top and brown.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, saute beef in margarine with garlic, onions and mushrooms until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Add flour; mix until blended.
Add beef broth, salt, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Blend in sour cream.
Do not boil, but keep warm.

title: chicken breasts with cheese and herbs
directions: Halve the breasts to make 8 pieces.
Remove skin and membrane and pound the breasts to make 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cut cheese into 8 strips.

title: marinated chevre (goat cheese)
directions: Place goat cheese (Chevre) on a plate.
Sprinkle dried or fresh herbs on top.
Pour olive oil over cheese and let marinate for at least 1 hour.
Serve with good quality crackers or French bread.

title: daiquiri punch
directions: In bowl, combine juice, rum and mix.
Pour in 7-Up and mix carefully.
Float lime slices on top.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not overbake.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water in a heavy pan; cook over heat until mixture reaches 300° or hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and add cinnamon oil and coloring.
Stir.

title: best ever date pudding
directions: Pour
this
batter
into
a
buttered
pan
(about
8 x 8-inch).
Cover
with a mixture of 1 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon of butter and 2 cups boiling water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: wild rice chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, rice, beans, mayonnaise and soup together; spread in long baking dish.
Bake at 350° until mixture starts to bubble. Take out; sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Put back in oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: makes own crust peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter and pour in square baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour over butter but do not mix! Spoon peaches over the top with juice.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve either warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: white house twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 400° oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Cut potatoes in half while still hot.
Remove the pulp.
Salt to taste.
Add horseradish, butter, sour cream and scallion.
Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Return to shell, top with melted butter and cover with paprika just before reheating potatoes in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Flatten chicken breasts slightly and place a slice of bacon on each chicken breast; roll up.
Lay on dried beef in pan. Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake 3 hours in 250° oven.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onions.
Press biscuits into muffin pan.
Spoon mixture into cups. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend ingredients.
Grease and flour bottom of 3 small bread pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans on cooling rack.

title: crispy baked spud halves
directions: Scrub and dry potato.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Brush cut surfaces with a mixture of lemon juice and melted margarine.
Dip in a mixture of Parmesan cheese, basil leaves and pepper.
Bake cut sides down on a greased heavy baking sheet in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until tender and browned.
Serve with sour cream on top.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Clean and chop potatoes and eggs into small pieces.
Chop green pepper, radishes and onion fine.
Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: tarragon wafers
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Beat in egg and stir in sesame seed, pecans and tarragon.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the mixture; mix well.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Blend all ingredients together; chill.
With floured hands, shape into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a chilled glass, dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 350°.
Nuts, raisins and dates are optional.

title: sausage macaroni stir-fry
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add smoked sausage and carrot; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Stir-fry just until tender.
Stir in macaroni; heat through.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: In medium bowl beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand, then stir in ReaLemon.
Pour into crust.

title: melon punch
directions: Put all in a blender and puree.
Serve with lots of ice. Serves 8.

title: rice and hamburger casserole
directions: Bring the rice to a boil, then let simmer.
Brown hamburger, onion and add celery.
Add soups, brown sugar, soy sauce and two cups of celery water.
Mix together and put in casserole, covered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken/cream of celery soup

title: jamaica whelk fritters
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Make a well in center.
Add beaten egg and 1/2 the milk.
Blend well and gradually add the rest of the milk, onion, pepper and tomato.
Blend and let batter rest for 1/2 hour.

title: frankfurters in blankets
directions: Roll out dough; cut in 4-inch squares.
Lay weinie on each square and roll up.
Moisten edges and pinch together.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown. Serve with mustard sauce.

title: lemony cheese cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix crumbs of cookies, cinnamon and margarine in small bowl.
Press into bottom and about 1 1/2 to 2-inches up sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate.

title: pat mercers brunswick stew
directions: Stew chicken in large pot or pressure cooker.
Remove chicken. Add onions and potatoes to the broth and cook until done.
Add boned chicken, cut in bite size pieces, ground meat and other ingredients.
Simmer over low heat until thick (about 2 to 3 hours).
If too thick, thin with chicken bouillon.
If too thin, use 2 to 3 tablespoons cornstarch mixed with 1/2 cup water or liquid from stew.

title: steak burgundy
directions: While rice is cooking, saute steak in oil until brown.
Add onions and cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir in carrots, wine, broth, mushrooms with liquid and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery and continue cooking 10 minutes longer.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water. Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over bed of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio mini loaves
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake and pudding mixes. Add sour cream, eggs, oil and water. Beat until blended. Pour into five greased 5 3/4 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans. Combine the pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks. Yield: 5 loaves.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and juice.
Chill.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: buttermilk biscuit
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Blend in shortening.
Add buttermilk.
Knead over several times on floured board.
Press out and leave thick.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart baking dish, combine water, wild rice and bouillon; set aside.
In large skillet, brown meat; pour off fat.
Stir in celery, onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Add soup, long grain rice and pepper.
Add meat mixture to wild rice mixture; mix well.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes. Serve hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line dish sparingly with broken corn tortillas.
Layer ingredients.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Put grated cheese (both kinds) into pie shell.
Take chopped onion and saute in butter in pan.
Add onion to cheese.
Mix together eggs and cream.
Add a dash of nutmeg.
Pour eggs, cream and nutmeg into pie shell with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: florida shrimp bake
directions: Arrange shrimp in one layer in a shallow baking dish.
In a saucepan, melt butter and add lemon juice, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, hot red pepper flakes and salt.
Reserve 4 tablespoons, then pour remaining mixture over the shrimp.
Add the reserved butter mixture to cracker crumbs and mix well.
Sprinkle crumbs over the shrimp and bake in a 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato-bacon frittata
directions: Brown bacon until crisp and drain. Pour off most of bacon fat from pan and cook potatoes, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper until potatoes are tender. Grease 10-inch quiche or 9 x 9-inch baking dish and preheat oven to 375°. In a bowl, mix eggs, milk, Bisquick, cheese, butter and salt and pepper to taste. Combine with potatoes and bacon. Pour in pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Dip chicken in butter; roll in cracker crumbs.
Place pieces on foil; cover with another piece of foil and seal edges.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: fruity-fruit salad
directions: Mix jello according to package directions in large mixing bowl. Place in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Mix fruit and nuts in jello and pour in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Return to refrigerator until completely jelled.
Spread thawed Cool Whip over top of salad and keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: hobo meal
directions: Place each pork chop on a piece of aluminum foil; salt and pepper to taste.
Place sliced onions, potatoes, carrots and celery on top.
It is best to salt and pepper each layer just a little.
Close aluminum foil; place each meal on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: In medium size bowl, combine brown sugar and teriyaki sauce. Stir well.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix in wingettes and marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly; spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30-35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: milky way cake
directions: Stir bars and 2 tablespoons of water in medium pan over low heat until smooth; cool slightly.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.

title: american goulash
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cook beef and onion in 1 tablespoon margarine until meat loses its red color, breaking up with a fork. Add cooked macaroni, seasonings, tomatoes and soup.
Mix well.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Mix crumbs with 3 tablespoons melted margarine and sprinkle on top of mixture in dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: indian tacos
directions: Thaw 1 loaf of frozen bread and cut into 8 slices.
Roll or pat out thin; fry (in small amount of fat) on each side until brown.
On each slice, spread some ground beef, taco sauce, onion, pepper, lettuce, tomatoes and grated cheese.

title: red punch
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate until serving time. Pour into punch bowl and float orange slices with cherry on top of punch.

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Slowly mix in flour with the baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in the bananas (nuts if desired).
Grandma also adds about 1/2 cup chopped cherries.
(She says it looks nicer!)
You may also add about 1/2 cup milk to make into muffins instead of bread.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake bread at 325° for 1/2 hour, then increase to about 400° for 1/2 hour (1 hour total).

title: white bread
directions: In large bowl put sugar, oil, and salt.

In a quart jar fill with warm, (not boiling) water. Add yeast. In a measuring cup pour 1 c. of the warm water. Set aside. In measuring cup add 2 pkg. quick-rise yeast, 1 tsp. sugar and 1 tsp. flour. Stir with small whisk and set aside until double.

title: reese's peanut butter cup oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Add granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; blend into peanut butter mixture.
Stir in oats.
Cover dough; refrigerate several hours or until firm enough to handle.

title: rice soup with shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Slice parsley and ginger into small pieces.
Boil water in a saucepan over high heat.
Add rice.
Stir shortly.
Add shrimp, sugar, m.s.g., fish sauce, celery salt, black pepper and eggs.
Allow to boil for 1 minute.
Cover with lid and remove from heat.

title: summer squash
directions: Slice squash and cook until tender.
Saute onion in 1/2 cup margarine and mix with squash.
Add 15 crumbled crackers, eggs, seasonings and cheese.
Place mixture in a 2-quart casserole.

title: date balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Bring to slow boil for 4 minutes. Do not overcook; will harden.
Take from heat; stir in chopped nuts and 2 cups Rice Krispies.
When cool enough to handle, roll into balls, then in powdered sugar.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: dr. hall's chili
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add tomato soup and beans.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into one 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: best orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice. Add fruit and pecans.
Chill.
This makes a small ring mold.
Can be doubled for a large mold.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first three ingredients until creamy.
Add water and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well; cover and chill 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350`.
Shape in 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with tines of fork dipped in sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from pan to wire rack.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: caraway fettuccine(low-fat)
directions: Combine milk and margarine in a saucepan; place over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until margarine melts.
Add fettuccine and remaining ingredients.
Cook, tossing gently, until thoroughly heated.
Yield: 4 servings (3.9 g per 3/4 cup serving).

title: homemade cherry pie filling
directions: In a saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Gradually stir in juice from canned cherries and cook until thickened, adding cherries and flavorings at the end.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed. Soften cream cheese and blend with sugar until smooth. Blend prepared Dream Whip in cheese mixture. Spoon into pie crust or graham cracker crust. Top with cherry pie filling. Chill 3 hours or more.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water.
Stir well.
Add sugar and lemon juice, stir well.
Add pineapple with juice.
Stir and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in 3/4 of the Cool Whip.

title: creamy pineapple-coconut punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, club soda and cream of coconut in a punch bowl or pitcher.
Stir until well blended.
Serve in punch cups with a flavored ice cube in each.

title: special seasoning
directions: Mix together and store in a spice container.
This seasoning mix is great for seasoning simple dishes, makes them taste elegant.
It is especially good with rice.

title: hot sausage and black-eyed peas
directions: Chop onions and peppers and saute in large skillet.
Add peas and tomato juice;
simmer 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order, starting with lettuce, then cauliflower.
Seal with little less than 2 cups mayo.
Add onion, bacon, Cheddar cheese and sugar;
spread this on top of cauliflower mixture. Chill.
Can sit overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls on large cookie sheet according to directions.
Cool.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and mayo; beat until smooth.
Add dressing (dry).
Spread on cool crust.

title: seasoned sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, stuffing mix, eggs and cheese together.
Form in small balls.
Wrap with bacon and hold together with toothpick. Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: zucchini and rice casserole
directions: In 2-quart buttered casserole, layer zucchini, rice and cheese twice. In a saucepan, combine soup, 1 soup can of water, salt and pepper. Heat, then pour over casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 more minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Place slices of cookie dough around pizza pan; press down to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients together; then spread over cooled cookie crust.
Before slicing fruit, boil the next 4 ingredients.
When thickened, let cool.
Slice and arrange fruit on cream cheese layer.
Pour orange juice glaze over fruit and let cool in refrigerator.

title: chicken with salsa
directions: Brown chicken pieces and put in baking dish.
Spoon over top of each piece, 1 tablespoon salsa, 1 tablespoon sour cream and 1 tablespoon grated cheese (can use Jack or Mozzarella).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses warm to room temperature.
Knead it.
Form ball and roll in crushed walnuts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients,
roll into balls and chill.
In double boiler melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Dip in balls.
Set on foil.

title: sirlion tip roast
directions: Wash roast. Put in pan and cover with water. Add salt, pepper and bouillon. Let cook on stove until tender.
Add flour and cook until gravy is smooth.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes. Mix with rest of ingredients. Put in casserole pan. Spoon on topping.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Drain beans and add sugar and all ingredients except onions. Place onion rings on top.
Simmer for 3 hours.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix the ingredients and pile lightly in prepared shells.
Bake in a hot oven for 10 minutes.

title: japanese chocolate pies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together; add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into 2 uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Put part of softened ice cream in large punch bowl.
Add one can pineapple juice and mix until slushy.
In separate bowl, mix partially softened sherbet and remaining pineapple juice until slushy.
Add this mixture to punch bowl and blend well.
Just before serving, pour ginger ale carefully in bowl, stirring gently.
Serve at once.

title: peanut butter brownie trifle
directions: Prepare and bake brownies according to package direction. Cool completely. Cut into 3/4 in. pieces using sharp knife.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Place the dry rice in small casserole.
Mix in the consomme. Place the browned pork chops on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Five minutes before baking is complete, spread the onion rings on top and bake for remaining time, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray 2-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Place stuffing and French fried onions (1/2 can) in the bottom of dish.
Layer broccoli over stuffing, then chicken.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of milk and sour cream; pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add 1/2 can of French fried onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet (1 can per sheet). Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 400°. Set aside to cool. Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dip mix. Spread on cooked rolls. Top with chopped vegetables. Sprinkle shredded cheese last. Chill and serve.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix butter, flour, pecans and vanilla together.
Roll into balls and bake at 320° for 30 minutes.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8-inch pans and line bottoms with wax paper.

title: salmon dip
directions: Drain salmon, remove skin and mix.
Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix sugar, pinch of salt, cocoa and flour together.
Separate eggs.
Mix yolks and milk together, then mix with dry ingredients. Add margarine.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Add vanilla and pour into baked shell.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown sausage; set aside.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in oil.
Add chili powder and cumin and stir to distribute. Add drained beans, tomatoes and picante sauce and sausage. Simmer until heated through.
Eat as is or serve over rice or add 1 cup cooked rice to mixture.

title: cherrie crunch
directions: For crust, mix butter and flour.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Combine other ingredients and pour in crust.
Top with fruit and chill.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Grate cucumbers; strain off juice.
To the pulp, add remaining ingredients.

title: banana split delight
directions: Crush the vanilla wafers and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the sugar, eggs, melted margarine and vanilla.
Beat with a mixer for 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Split the bananas lengthwise and dip into pineapple juice.
Place over creamed mixture.
Drain pineapple and pour over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top and then nuts.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk together.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter over the melted butter.
Add fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Serves 6.

title: turkey and sausage casserole(a great holiday brunch dish.)
directions: Saute sausage until brown (Swift Brown 'N Serve links work well; cut in 4 pieces after browning).
Bulk sausage may be cut in bite size pieces.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes and put in buttered casserole dish. Melt margarine.
Add flour and stir in milk until smooth and bubbly. Pour over potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: extra special macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
(Do not overcook.)
Mix in pimentos, mushrooms, onion, cheese, mayonnaise and soup.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Put pats of butter on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with Ritz crackers and 1 stick oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttery bubble bread
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 1 cup flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled. Punch dough down. Turn onto a lightly floured surface. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Dip the balls in butter and arrange in greased 9-inch fluted tube pan. Drizzle with remaining butter. Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Invert on serving platter.

title: shrimp pasta ala ronald
directions: In frying pan, saute with 1 ounce olive oil the diced garlic until it browns.
Add 7 ounces olive oil and chopped onions.
Cook until onions are clear, approximately 8 minutes.
Add zucchini, then shrimp, sugar, black pepper and dash of salt.
Cook approximately 5 minutes until shrimp are al dente.
Boil linguine approximately 6 minutes; strain.
Cover linguine with sauce and toss.
Bon appetit!

title: oatmeal tube cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Cream butter and sugars; beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats mixture; mix well.
Stir together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in pecans and coconut.

title: cottage cheese casserole
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in a large skillet.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Simmer until macaroni is tender, about 25 minutes. Have parsley, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese ready.
Put half of the macaroni mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese and parsley. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease casserole dish and layer chicken, tortilla chips and 1 cup of the grated cheese; set aside. Combine soup, tomatoes, broth, celery, garlic and onion in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle leftover cup of cheese over top.
Bake until cheese melts (5 to 8 minutes).

title: banana cream pie
directions: Sift together in top of double boiler, sugar, flour, gelatin and salt.
Add light cream; whisk until well combined.
Place over simmering water; add egg yolks.
Continue whisking until mixture starts to thicken.
Remove from double boiler and beat until smooth.
Stir in rum and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in sour cream; beat until smooth.
Place in refrigerator until mixture starts to set, 20 minutes.
Watch so it does not get too thick.
Line bottom of crust with banana slices; pour custard over and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Just before serving, top with whipped cream, confectioners sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; mix.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients. Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chris' low-fat party dip
directions: In medium casserole dish, layer in order all ingredients. Microwave until cheese is melted.
Top with low-fat sour cream and sliced green onions.
It goes fast.

title: chocolate-cherry dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and walnuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix together and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain, do not rinse.
Then add sugar and vinegar.
Let stand another 24 hours in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, then ready to eat or freeze.

title: beef sausage
directions: Mix well.
Form into thin patties.
Cook in oil on low heat.

title: corkscrew macaroni salad
directions: Prepare
macaroni
as label
directs.
Drain
and
cool slightly.
In large bowl, mix
mayonnaise,	vinegar
and milk. Stir in macaroni, cheese and corn.	Add
more milk, as needed, until desired consistency.	Cover
mixture	and refrigerate at least one hour to blend flavors.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour 2 cups of cold milk into bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Stir whipped topping and half of the crushed cookies into pudding very gently.
Place about 1 tablespoon of remaining crushed cookies into bottom of each plastic or paper cup.
Fill about 3/4 full with pudding mix.
Top each cup with the rest of the crushed cookies.
Put cups into refrigerator to chill for about 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 paper or plastic cupfuls.

title: fresh apple crunch
directions: Spread apples in 9 x 15-inch (2 1/2 to 3-quart) baking dish. Sprinkle spices, sugar and water.
Mix next 3 ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Spread pecans over topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If browns too fast, reduce heat to 325° for last 1/2 hour.
Serve hot with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: swedish chocolate balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut, in a large bowl.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll balls in shredded coconut.
Refrigerate until serving.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together well.
Drop onto cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce and refrigerate.
Mix all other ingredients you plan to use.
Walnuts can be browned in butter on the stove in saucepan, but to avoid fat and calories, best use them as they are.
Whatever ingredient combinations you use, this is a great salad.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water and cook cranberries until they pop.
Add gelatin, sugar and marshmallows. Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add fruit and nuts.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oatmeal and coconut cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs, oats, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift in flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Chill 3 hours.

title: chipped beef appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream; whip until fluffy.
Add onion and garlic; stir in dried beef.
Spread in a fairly small (3 cup) baking dish.
Top with pecans and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 20 minutes, until the pecans begin to brown and cheese is bubbling around the edges.
Serve hot with bread.
Serves approximately 20.

title: sheriff's stew
directions: Dilute each can of soup with a can of water.
Add rice.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add to soup mixture.
Slice sausages and add to mixture; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: prudy's kids' favorite cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add the liquids, beating 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. This is a moist, heavy cake.
Great to use sprinkled with powdered sugar to cut up for kids' "cut out cake" designs, layered with ice cream for "ice cream cakes" or, best of all, with the frosting below!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Add oil and water.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in grated chocolate and 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan. When still slightly warm, sprinkle shaved chocolate on top.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add milk and blend.
Pour into crust; top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with peanuts (if desired).
Chill.

title: poor people pate
directions: Drain and debone sardines.
Blend sardines with cream cheese. Add eggs, lemon juice and seasonings.
Blend well.
It should be fairly stiff.
Mold the mix on a plate and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: black raspberry vinegar
directions: For one quart, combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and let stand for at least 3 hours before use.
After 2 to 3 weeks, remove the garlic clove.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the first 5 ingredients together until it looks like cake batter.
Pour mix into pan.
Drain peaches and put on top of batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a large pan.
Cook over high heat, stirring until syrup tests to 230°.
Add peanuts and salt, stirring down when boils up.
Cook to 290°.
Remove from fire and add soda mixed with 1 teaspoon water, butter and flavoring.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour on marbled slab or buttered cookie sheet, pulling to thin out (wear gloves).
Cool before breaking.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all except 2/3 cup soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain and cover with rest of soup and cheese.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: spanish rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Hollow out French rolls and fill with mixture. Individually wrap rolls in wax paper.
Heat in 250° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: With mixer, beat together all ingredients for 4 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done with toothpick. Cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and set aside.
Mix catsup, mustard, onion and molasses together.
Stir hamburger, catsup mix and pork and beans together.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheeses get room temperature.
Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Chop pecans and roll cheese balls in chopped pecans.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Place bananas, eggs, butter, buttermilk or sour cream, lemon juice and sugar into blender.
Whirl until smooth.
In a bowl, mix together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Pour banana mixture over flour mixture.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 4-inch bread pan or two 3 x 7-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken pieces in 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven. Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes and water/broth over pieces.
Heat to boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in rice, ham and spices.
Heat to boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add frozen peas, artichoke hearts and a little salt.
Heat to boil; cover and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and olives.
Mix in separate bowl sour cream, vinegar and sugar.
Mix cucumber mixture with sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: blackberry cobbler(can substitute peach, strawberry or apple)
directions: Wash and drain berries.
In large saucepan, combine berries, water and 1/2 to 1 cup sugar.
Cook until mixture is hot and sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then add milk and vanilla.
Add bread and raisins.
Put into a buttered casserole. Add the milk mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Put casserole in pan of water.
Bake 10 minutes in a 450° oven, then 40 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: four winds casserole
directions: In large skillet heat oil.
Add onion and water chestnuts and saute until onion is soft.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup noodles.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine sugars, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Mix with eggs.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and top with miniature chocolate chips.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then add bananas and nuts.
Stir in well.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2).
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool slightly before removing from pans.

title: beef and cabbage taco casserole
directions: Mix

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, salt and sugar.
Blend in sour milk and beaten eggs.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Add together with bananas.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, salsa and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over chips.
Top with onions and olives.
Serves 6.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients, then roll (jelly roll technique), wrapping tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Cut remaining into 1-inch slices.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: bavarian angel cake
directions: Make a thin custard of first 5 ingredients.
Then dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and stir in custard (after removing from stove) while still hot.
Let cool and fold in 1 pint whipped cream of Cool Whip topping and egg whites, beaten stiff.
Break up angel food cake into pieces about the size of walnuts.
Line a large pan 3 or 4 inches deep with the cake.
Pour custard flavored with almond extract over the cake.
Repeat until pan is full.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
A few hours before serving, ice with 1/2 pint whipped cream of topping.
Cut in squares and serve with cherry on top.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Chop onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery and saute.
Add tomato paste, stewed tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Clean and devein shrimp.
Bring sauce to a boil, now add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp is cooked.
Serve over bed of rice.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add ice water and stir lightly.
(Dough will be just moist enough to cling together when pressed into a ball.)
Turn dough out on a lightly floured board or cloth.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness; trim to 1/2-inch larger than casserole dish.

title: spiced hot tea
directions: Steep tea bags in 8 cups water for 15 minutes.
Boil 2 cups water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Put all together.
Can be kept in crock-pot.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown beef.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients and simmer on low heat at least 1 hour, or put in slow cooker to cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: slow-cooker roast beef
directions: Coat roast with flour.
Place in slow cooker.
Combine soup mix, gravy mix, remaining flour and ginger ale in bowl; mix well. Pour over roast and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until tender.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and Velveeta cheese.
Add drained Veg-All.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add crumbled crackers.
Place on top of other mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pure di patate al limone(mashed potato with lemon)
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut them in equal-size pieces.
Put them into a saucepan and cover with milk and water.
Add large pinch of salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer gently until soft.
Drain and mash to a smooth puree.
Stir in the butter and lemon rind; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve at once.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cooked and drained macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper in alternate layers in buttered oblong baking dish, ending with layer of cheese on top.
Pour milk over all. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab meat baked in a ramekin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Combine all ingredients except fresh bread crumbs and divide among 6 lightly buttered 8-ounce ramekins. Cover lightly with bread crumbs and top with thin dots of butter. Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until crumbs are golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: baked peppers
directions: Fry ground meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook onion, celery and green peppers in water until tender, 15 or 20 minutes. Soak French bread or white bread in milk or water to soften.
Beat eggs well and add all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper.
Cut peppers in half.
Add filling.
Add small amount water to large baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Until firm and brown.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs*, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Spread all but 1 1/2 cups batter on greased 14 x 17-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Drop the rest of the batter by spoonfuls over cherries.

title: upstate minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage crosswise about 1/2-inch thick.
In a large kettle, brown sausage in oil.
Add onions, garlic, carrots and basil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, liquid bouillon and cabbage.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add beans and their liquid; cook another 20 minutes.

title: english muffins
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs well.
In another bowl mix sour milk and soda.
Sift together flour, allspice, nutmeg and cinnamon. Alternate milk and flour in mixing bowl with sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add oatmeal, chopped nuts and raisins or dates.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sprout burgers
directions: Mix ground beef, bean sprouts, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and garlic salt.
Make into patties.
Fry in skillet with oil.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in a greased and floured pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Combine salmon, cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill.
When firm enough to handle, form into a ball.
Roll in pecans and parsley.
Chill well.

title: cranberry sparkle punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
Add ice or ice ring.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Clean and wash vegetables and chop. Wash and soak wheat 10 minutes. Squeeze water from wheat and add to vegetables. Add lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper and mix well. Serve over lettuce (romaine).

title: devil's food cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Cook for 8 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.
Spread vanilla icing and put cookies together.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Combine in bowl the butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and cake mix.
Bake half in a 9 x 13-inch greased or sprayed pan for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add sugar.
Fold in the floured dates, nuts, vanilla and coconut (if using it). Drop on cookie sheet covered with wax paper, using a teaspoon. Bake at 325° until delicately browned.
The coconut makes the cookie quite moist and it adds flavor, but it is not necessary to make a good cookie.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In small bowl, beat egg until fluffy; add oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add both mixtures and mix, but leave batter lumpy.
Let stand 5 minutes before using.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all above ingredients together.
Put in glass bowl. Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and margarine. Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture on bottom and 2 inches up sides of 9-inch springform pan.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and marshmallow cream until smooth.
Add drained fruit; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: easy-time squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well. Add flour and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Grease jelly roll pan well and spread batter with a knife.
With knife, cut through batter to make 24 squares.
Place a generous tablespoon of fruit on each square and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with 10x powdered sugar and let cool.
Cut squares again.
I use two different fruits, making 12 of each.

title: file gumbo
directions: In a large pot, heat oil until hot.
Add flour and stir constantly until roux is dark brown.
Do this on low heat.
Add onion and green onions.
Let cook 10 minutes.
Add ham and let cook 5 minutes.
Add warmed stock and if necessary, additional water (about 1 gallon).
Bring to a boil and add chicken, turkey, oysters and shrimp.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Also season with parsley, thyme and crushed red pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes. Bring to a boil; turn heat off and ladel in file (about 2 tablespoons).
Serve over rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Prebake unpricked shell in 425° oven 4 to 5 minutes. Blend together eggs, sugar, melted and cooled butter, flour and vanilla. Gradually stir in buttermilk. Pour into shell and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on rack. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan (I use spray Pam).
Sprinkle nuts on bottom. Place frozen rolls evenly in pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Mix melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together and pour over rolls.
Cover with towel and let stand overnight.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frito pie
directions: Alternate layers, beginning and ending with Fritos.
Bake at 350°.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Boil oleo, milk and sugar 6 minutes.
Chop marshmallows; dissolve.
Add pecans.
Drop on waxed pepper or pour into 9 x 11-inch greased pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in saucepan. Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Mix quickly. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill. Makes 3 dozen.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate; form a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix together.
Can be used to marinate all meats.
I make up a large amount and store it in the refrigerator.
You can marinate meat in a zip lock bag for easier handling.

title: butter sponge cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks. Blend in mixer on slow speed for 10 minutes. Add flour, baking powder, lemon juice and grated lemon rind. Carefully fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or tester comes out clean.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan; cool slightly. Cream sugar and softened butter in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add mixture of flour and soda alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Add candy mixture and pecans; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add shredded cheese. Cut in shortening until well blended.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter or in squares with a knife.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 425° (hot oven) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 (2-inch) biscuits.
Serve immediately. Serves 12.

title: green beans and hamburger
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion in a skillet until brown and tender.
Stir in garlic, 1 1/2 cups water, soy sauce and molasses. Heat to boiling.
Add green beans and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and 1/4 cup of water.
Stir into mixture well.
Cook and stir until thick and boil for 1 minute.
Serve on rice and garnish with onion rings.

title: royal seafood casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well. Rinse with cold water.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Set aside.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake - no bake
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with plastic wrap.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk in a medium size bowl.
Pour cappuccino in bowl.
Quickly dip cookies, one at a time, into cappuccino, then spread one side with cream cheese mixture.
Arrange in a lined pan, starting from right to left, placing 5 cookies, spread side down, overlapping in a row.
Place next row of cookies from left to right.
Repeat until 4 rows of cookies cover bottom of pan.
Rotate pan 1/4 turn and add another layer of cookies.
Repeat rotating pan 1/4 turn and layering 2 more times for a total of 4 layers.
Pour any remaining cappuccino over the top.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour for flavors to blend.

title: beef stroganoff over noodles
directions: Put beef cubes and enough water to cover beef in roaster pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain off broth and keep.
Mix together mushrooms and soups; pour over beef cubes.
If more liquid is needed, use drained broth.
Cover and return to oven for 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Thicken with cornstarch, if needed.
Add Kitchen Bouquet if darker broth is desired.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put in a large saucepan and cook until meat is tender.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form round ball.
Wrap with corned beef. Let sit overnight.

title: candy-coated pretzels or fruit
directions: Melt candy coating in microwave.
Dip pretzels, cherries with stems, large fresh strawberries or other fruit.
Place on wax paper.
Chill for 30 minutes. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: radish onion spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in medium mixing bowl on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in radishes and chives.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: peachy cheese cake
directions: Make in 9-inch pie plate.
Blend crumbs, sugar, cinnamon and oleo.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of crumbs. Evenly line bottom and sides of pie plate, refrigerate.
Let cream cheese soften.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy, gradually add condensed milk until blended.
Blend in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour filling into chilled crust.
Arrange peaches on top.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in casserole.
Mix potato soup and sour cream. Spread on top of frozen potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and reserve juice.
Cream the cheese and juice. Add lemon juice, onion, crabmeat and half of the shrimp.
Fold in last of shrimp.
Serve hot or cold with Ritz crackers or chips. Will keep in fridge 1 to 2 weeks.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skin.
Peel and slice.
Fry bacon and set aside.
Cook onion in bacon fat.
Add flour, salt, celery seed, water and vinegar to onion and cook until it boils.
Boil one minute.
Pour over potatoes and add bacon.
Cover and let stand.
Serve warm.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Bring mustard, turmeric, salt, sugar, water and vinegar to a boil in saucepan.
Pour hot mixture over prepared vegetables.
Let stand 2 days in refrigerator before serving.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Drop mixture into hot greased skillet.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls according to package instructions.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing on high speed. Spread on top of lukewarm crescent rolls.
Sprinkle on vegetables and top with cheese.

title: kielbasa soup
directions: Add all ingredients except potatoes to the boiling water. When water boils again, reduce to medium heat and simmer for 1-1/2 hours. When carrots are tender, add potatoes. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: mock chocolate eclair
directions: Layer graham crackers in rectangular dish.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture over graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top of mixture. Spread chocolate frosting on graham crackers.
