Sprinkle nuts and place cherries on top of frosting. Store in refrigerator. Serve cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter well and blend in sugar and egg, beating vigorously until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, then flour mixture, and mix well.
Slowly fold in egg white and water.
Stir again until smooth.
Chill dough for 2 hours, then shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip fork in cold water and press balls out until flat.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: mrs. johnson's chicken
directions: Fry chicken to a golden brown.
Put in casserole dish.
Make white sauce in separate pan.
Add bay leaves, salt and pepper to taste and mushrooms.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken in casserole (use a deep dish).
If chicken isn't covered, pour over some milk and push meat up and down to mix.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, covered.
Serve with rice.

title: special hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate morsels, sugar, water and cinnamon in 4-cup measuring cup.
Microwave at Medium (50%) 2 to 3 minutes until chocolate is melted, stirring twice.
Cool to lukewarm.
Whip cream in small mixing bowl until stiff peaks form.
Gradually, whip in cooled chocolate mixture.
Chill.
(Chocolate mixture keeps well in refrigerator in covered container up to 1 week.)

title: tin roof pie
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, combine peanut butter and corn syrup. Add cereal and mix until well combined.
Press in bottom and up sides of plate. Chill. Spoon softened ice cream into shell. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving. Serve with warm chocolate syrup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: daffodil dip
directions: Mix all together and set overnight, if possible.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water until forms a soft ball when tested in cold water, then pour over stiffly beaten egg whites. Beat until cool.
Add nuts and cherries if desired.

title: spice cake
directions: Put sugar, lard, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and water in a pan; cook 3 minutes.
Cool.
Put in soda and salt.
Then add flour and baking powder, just enough flour to make a batter, not too stiff and bake.

title: lemon-strawberry waffles
directions: Turn on waffle iron.
Use utility knife to cut tops off strawberries on cutting board.
Cut berries into thin slices and place in serving bowl.
Place frying pan on burner; add margarine and melt slowly over low heat.
Turn off burner.

title: eggless raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Cook down to 1 cup water; let cool. Blend in sugar and shortening or oil.
When cool enough, add flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake until done; let cool and turn out of pan.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients into blender and mix well.

title: holiday pumpkin loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease (three) 3 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Add hot water to raisins and set aside; cool.
Mix (with electric mixer) shortening, sugar and molasses until light and fluffy.
Then on low speed, beat in eggs and pumpkin.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and toss in chopped nuts. Gradually beat flour-nut mixture into creamed mixture and add raisins and water.
Mix until all dry ingredients are moistened. Pour batter into loaf pans (evenly divided) and bake 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes, then turn out of pan and cool on rack.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Drain zucchini well, pressing between layers of paper towels. Combine zucchini and next five ingredients in a large bowl. Divide in patties (mixture will be soft). Pour oil to depth of 1/2-inch in heavy skillet. Fry in hot oil over medium heat for 2 minutes each side. Drain on paper towels.

title: apple salad
directions: Core and chop apples.
Combine apples, raisins, celery and nuts.
Blend orange juice with yogurt.
Pour over apple mixture and toss well.
Place on a bed of lettuce; garnish with cinnamon and serve.

title: deer roast
directions: Take deer roast and marinate overnight in some wine, turning 2 to 3 times.
Put in oven the next day and roast just like a beef roast.
Bake 2 to 3 hours or until tender in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and let stand until cool.
Serve.

title: cheese kolacky(polish)
directions: Cream shortening.
Mix in 1 package cream cheese at a time. Add flour.
Continue mixing by hand until mixture works away from side of bowl. Cover with waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll a small portion at a time in a cool place on powdered sugar until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in squares or rounds. Fill with favorite filling (Solo in cans works well).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: beef and beer stew
directions: Melt butter in large saucepot or Dutch oven.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes to brown slightly.
Add carrots, herbs and garlic. Continue to cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour, tomato paste, consomme and beer.
Add cooked meat and cover. Simmer 1/2 hour or until carrots are tender.
Serves 6.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine rice and vermicelli with ground beef and egg.
Shape into small meatballs (approximately 20).
Heat oil in skillet and brown meatballs on all sides.
Combine contents of flavor packet with water.
Pour over meatballs and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken gravy, if desired.
Makes approximately 20 meatballs.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix taco seasoning into browned ground beef.
Set aside.
In a greased deep casserole dish, lay tortillas in bottom, overlapping to cover entire bottom of dish.
Spread 1/2 of meat mixture over tortillas evenly and sprinkle 1/2 of cheese evenly.
Continue with another layer of tortillas; then meat and then cheese.
Pour tomato juice over entire surface, then bake in a 350° oven until heated and cheese is melted (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Serve on bed of lettuce and top with sour cream and diced tomatoes and onions.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: first class hash
directions: Mix together ingredients and turn into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Grate cheese. Let cream cheese soften. Chop nuts. Cream all the ingredients together. Roll into logs and sprinkle on chili powder.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix sauerkraut, carrots, celery, green pepper, onion and pimientos.
Combine sugar and oil in small bowl, mixing well into the vegetables. Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half of the potatoes in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of each ingredient.
Repeat the procedure and add milk so that potatoes are just covered.
Cover; bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Remove cover; continue to bake 40 minutes longer or until tender-brown.
Serves 6.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Wash, trim and pare carrots.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
In a casserole combine carrots and water.
Cover.
Microwave at Full power for 12 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.
Drain and return to casserole.
Stir in margarine and cinnamon.
Drizzle with honey.
Mix gently.
Cover and microwave for 30 seconds and sprinkle with pecans.
Serves 4.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cream shortening, sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla and butter flavoring. Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring. Add to first mixture. Alternately add flour and buttermilk. Mix vinegar and soda in a small bowl. Add to batter; blend. Bake in three 9 or 10 inch round cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Let cool completely. Cover with frosting.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine egg yolks with starch, sugar and water.
Mix into paste, pour in milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring continuously until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat in vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Pour into a baked 9-inch crust.
May top with chocolate syrup (optional).

title: jello cheese salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar and boil 3 minutes.
Mix Jell-O and hot water; cool.
Add shredded cheese and nuts.
Let this partially congeal and add small Cool Whip; chill.

title: frozen lime butter mint salad
directions: Mix pineapple, jello and marshmallows in large bowl.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning whip cream and fold into jello mixture with crushed mints.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Cover and freeze.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Wash, dry and skin pieces of chicken, if not skinned.
Blend corn flake crumbs and Parmesan cheese (2 cups crumbs to 1/4 cup Parmesan).
Dip chicken in Kraft Lite Italian dressing, then roll in the cereal crumb mixture.
Place in a baking dish or pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover the pan; bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until tender.
Time depends on the amount of chicken.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spray a shallow casserole dish with vegetable spray.
In casserole, spread pineapple.
Mix sugar, flour and reserved juice; pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix together melted margarine and crushed crackers; sprinkle over pineapple and cheese. Bake at 350° until hot and lightly browned.

title: cocoa krispies chocolate nut treats
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with butter.

title: mediterranean hye roller
directions: Cover entire round of bread with cream cheese.
Spread hummus over 3/4 of the cream cheese, leaving about 4 inches at one end with cream cheese only.
Cover hummus with fresh spinach leaves. Continue to layer ingredients and roll bread into jelly roll. Chill for one hour.
Cut roll on bias and serve.
This should be served the same day it is made.

title: green rice(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart casserole combine green onions, butter, bell pepper and parsley.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in bouillon and pepper.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture is boiling.
Stir in rice. Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 14 to 16 minutes or until rice is done.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Cooking time:
23 to 25 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes. Add next 4 ingredients. Fold in beaten egg whites. Fry until brown on each side.

title: spinach and feta cheese-stuffed pasta shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Squeeze spinach dry.
Transfer spinach to a large bowl.
Add Ricotta, 1/2 cup Parmesan, Feta, basil and garlic to bowl.
Season mixture with salt and pepper.
Blend. Spoon 1/2 cup marinara sauce evenly over bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Fill each pasta shell with spinach mixture. Place shells, filling side up, in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Cover loosely with foil and bake until heated through, about 30 minutes.
Use additional Parmesan cheese for garnish.
Yield:
Six servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake in 1 large or 2 small greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rhubarb or apple crunch
directions: Combine fruit, sugar and flour.
Put into a greased 8 X 8 pan.
Combine brown sugar, oatmeal, flour, butter and salt. Sprinkle over fruit and work in.
Bake at 370 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add raisins and pecans to sugar.
Add oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add figs last.
Bake in tube pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mema's chicken casserole
directions: Place tortillas on bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Layer chicken pieces, onion, chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese soup.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Drop about a teaspoon of mixture on lightly greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Let cool about 5 minutes and remove from cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Pour Karo syrup in pan, then add the sugar.
Stir; bring to a boil.
Boil at rolling boil for 1 minute.
Add the peanut butter and then corn flakes quickly.
Spread in pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.
Enjoy!

title: flour tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread in flour tortilla and roll up.
Slice each roll into bite size pieces and stick with toothpicks to hold together. Place on tray with hot sauce in the middle of tray in bowl for dipping tortilla in.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet or crock-pot.
Saute onion in margarine until tender and clear.
Add catsup, barbecue sauce and sugar. Stir until bubbly and sugar is dissolved.
Add chicken pieces that have been salted and peppered.
Pour Coke over the chicken. Reduce heat to simmer and cook for at least 1 hour (or longer for more tender chicken).
This recipe is also great for rabbit.

title: caramel orange ring
directions: Grease a Bundt pan or tube pan with 1 tablespoon softened butter. Dot orange marmalade around bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with pecans. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Separate biscuits.
Dip each one in melted butter and then in the brown sugar and cinnamon. Stand on edge around the pan, arranging them the way they are in the can.
Drizzle with any remaining butter and sprinkle with any leftover cinnamon mixture. Can be made to this point and covered and refrigerated to be baked later.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan for 5 minutes and turn onto a plate.

title: praline pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the chopped pecans over the bottom of pan; set aside.
Combine sugars, butter and shortening; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla, then fold in remaining 1 cup pecans.

title: communion bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cool to lukewarm.
While waiting, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add eggs and yeast to cooled mixture.
Add flour and knead.
Brush top with oil and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down.
Make into 2 loaves.
Knead and put into pans and brush top with oil.
Let rise another hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil and bake another 20 minutes.
Brush tops with margarine and take out of pans.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Alternate dry ingredients and applesauce.
Fill greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together first 10 ingredients thoroughly.
Spread into a greased and floured 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Combine all ingredients together and add whole mushrooms.
Keep covered and unrefrigerated for 3 to 5 days.

title: cheesy zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in fine slices and arrange in layers on cake pan or baking dish sprayed with nonstick coating:
first, a layer of zucchini, sprinkle of salt, oregano and onion flakes to taste; then a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat until only lacking last layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over layers, then last layer of Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at approximately 400° for about 20 minutes, or until cheese browns slightly.

title: round steak bake
directions: Spread soup mix over half the round steak.
Fold over; wrap tight in foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Mix 8 quart ground tomatoes with 1 cup salt.
Let drain in bag overnight.
In
the
morning, grind cabbage, green and red peppers and onions.
Mix all ingredients together in large kettle. Cook until onions are tender, about 20 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs; blend in milk, margarine, nutmeg and vanilla. Pour into dry ingredients and mix just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Optional:
Brush top with melted margarine and sprinkle with sugar.)
Makes 12 large muffins or 18 medium.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook in middle of oven until done at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, blending well.
Put into 2 greased pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: black bean soup
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add ham bone; heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 2 hours (do not boil or beans will burst).
Stir in carrot, celery, yellow onion, garlic, hot pepper, bay leaf and salt.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove ham bone and bay leaf.
Soup can be pressed through food mill or placed in blender container and blended until uniform consistency.
Trim ham bone and stir meat into soup.
Serve with lemon slice, shredded eggs and chopped red onion.
Stir in wine, if desired.
Serves 6 (one cup servings).

title: manju
directions: Combine ingredients and knead until thoroughly mixed.
Make approximately 2-inch balls.
Flatten dough and place Koshian filling in the center.
Fold dough over filling, pinching ends to form a ball.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: venezuelan potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots and cut into bite size pieces. Combine the mayonnaise, mustard, sugar, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Add the chicken, potatoes, carrots and peas to the sauce mix. Stir well.

title: barbecue sauce and chipped ham
directions: In large frying pan, melt oleo.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for a few minutes. Add chipped ham and simmer until heated through.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook ground beef; add chopped onion and bacon until done.
Add pork and beans, sugar, catsup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Pour into baking dish; bake in 375° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
Add salt, baking soda, vanilla and flour and mix with hand mixer.
Add chocolate chips and stir with a spoon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: joan's sugared peanuts
directions: Heat water and sugar in iron skillet until sugar dissolves in water.
Add peanuts and cook until peanuts are well coated with mixture.
Pour peanuts onto a greased pan with sides, like a jelly roll pan.
Cook at 350° in oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until peanuts taste done.
Stir often.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with Melba toast or Club crackers.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon in pot.
Add onion; continue cooking until onion is transparent.
Add other ingredients.
Serve warm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Pour in hot iron skillet (save a little of
the
oil
to
put in skillet).
Bake at 400° until brown and firm.

title: the easiest pound cake ever
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown beef and onion; pour off fat and mix with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Layer cut-up chicken and broccoli in a dish.
Slice cheese; layer on top.
Pour soup over.
Top with stuffing mix (prepared according to package).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Mix together salad oil, lemon pepper, wine vinegar, lemon juice, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Marinate roast in mixture for 1 to 2 days, turning at least once a day.
Cook, uncovered, with marinade in a Dutch oven at 250° for 3 hours. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and serve with heated marinade. Also good served hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening and sugar.
Stir in flour. Press and flatten with hand to cover bottom of ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 10 minutes and then spread with topping.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Heat milk to just under boiling point. Add all ingredients, except the green onions and bacon. Use onions and bacon as garnish and serve hot with crackers or rolls.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Put potatoes in dish to defrost, just to separate.
Add other ingredients except corn flake crumbs.
Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: meatless chili
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring often. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer.
Stir occasionally 15 to 20 minutes, to blend flavors.
Makes 8 cups, 4 servings.

title: potatoes, onion and pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and slice as many potatoes as you need to serve.
Place potatoes in casserole dish or pan.
Sprinkle a little salt and pepper over potatoes.
Slice onions thin and put a layer on top of potatoes.
Brown pork chops, just a little, on both sides.
Place on top of onions.
Use as many pork chops as you need.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Cover with foil paper and cook at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: egg in a basket
directions: Tear a hole (the size of an egg yolk) in the center of a slice of bread.
In a frying pan, fry the bread until lightly browned on one side.
Turn bread over and crack an egg onto it so that the yolk falls into the hole and the white spreads out over the bread. Cook for a few minutes, then flip over and cook until done.

title: picante sauce
directions: Place in 2 qt saucepan cook for 25 min. Put in jars and process in hot water bath 15 min.

title: macaroni vegetable salad
directions: Pour macaroni into boiling salted water and cook as directed on macaroni box.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Combine macaroni with vegetables in bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: bread and butter pickle
directions: Mix 2 quarts ice cubes with cucumbers, onions, and salt.
Let stand for 3 hours and drain thoroughly.
Make a pickling syrup with the remaining ingredients and let come to a boil.
Add cucumber mixture and reheat to scalding, but do not boil.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend the sugar, corn syrup and butter in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to a boil.
Blend hot mixture into beaten eggs. Stir in pecans, vanilla and salt.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate almond wafers
directions: Mix well the sugar, salt and sifted cake flour. Add milk, vanilla, butter and eggs. Mix thoroughly after adding each.

title: allgood pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and cream.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk. Add flavoring.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake in large tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix sour cream & onion soup mix and mushrooms with spinach. Bake 300° for 20 minutes.
Put onion rings on top for last 10 minutes.

title: macadamia cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Add oil;
mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for ham and cheese.
Place meat mixture on a piece of 12 x 10-inch foil, spreading to cover, almost to the edges.
Lay ham on top and sprinkle cheese over all.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg lightly; add corn.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; add to mixture.
Fry in deep fat at 360° or 60 second bread test or on well-greased griddle.
Serves 4.

title: mom's cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers and salt and let set for 2 or more hours. Then drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients with cucumbers; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Will keep well.

title: fred's cheese ball
directions: Combine above and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.

title: indian hills dressing
directions: Shake in quart jar.
Place 2 whole cloves of garlic in jar. Let stand 24 hours, then remove garlic.

title: bread bowls
directions: In heavy duty mixer: place yeast, water, salt and flour.
Let beat for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Mix enough flour to make dough leave sides of bowl. Place in oiled bowl and cover.
Let rise until double.
When dough has doubled, punch down, let rest for 10 minutes.
Form into 7 ounce balls, place on oiled sheet pan sprinkled with corn meal.
Brush with a mixture of egg white and water. Place in a warm place until double.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for 20 minutes (until golden) cut circle from top and remove most of center.
Fill with hot soup.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine in usual manner.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: oliebollen(also called fat balls)
directions: Scald milk; add butter and the 1/4 cup sugar to milk and stir until butter is melted.
Set aside to cool.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients with mixer and roll into balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together and keep hot in double boiler.
Stick toothpick into center of balls and dip about 2/3 of ball into melted chocolate.
Depress buckeye top to cover toothpick hole.
Chill.

title: pot roast and gravy
directions: Mix beef and soup together.
Place roast in pan with cover that fits secure and snug.
Pour soup and beef mixture over roast and cover.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Don't open cover until done. The gravy is self made.
For larger roast, double all ingredients.

title: mrs. field's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix softened butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 22 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Stir onions, cabbage, peppers and tomatoes together.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt and soak overnight.
Place in colander and wash off under faucet.
Drain and combine sugar, celery seed, turmeric, mustard seed and vinegar.
Heat this mixture.
Pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling and cook 5 minutes.
May be cold packed before canning.
Process about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 pints. (Two cucumbers may be added also.)

title: red cabbage
directions: Combine cabbage, water, vinegar, butter or margarine, brown sugar, salt and nutmeg in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Peel and cut apples into fourths; add to cabbage mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes or until liquid evaporates and apples are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients (except vegetables to be used for dipping).
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and baking soda in large bowl; make well in center.
Mix oil, eggs and strawberries in medium bowl.
Add to well in dry ingredients, mixing by hand until mixed well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/4 hours or until loaves test done.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef, onion and green peppers.
Add tomatoes, sour cream, macaroni and seasoning.
Cover and bring to a boil; turn to simmer and steam for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a pan.
Refrigerate.

title: armenian pilaf
directions: Brown rice in butter in Dutch oven.
Add vermicelli and coat with butter.
Add onions.
Stir in broth and salt.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
Remove cover, stir rice carefully with a fork and bake 10 additional minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: chop suey
directions: Heat shortening; add onion until light brown and add meat until brown, then add mushrooms.
Pour boiling water over meat, immersing meat completely.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Keep adding boiling water to keep meat completely immersed at all times. After 1 hour of cooking, add celery, salt and pepper.
Last half hour, thicken with flour and water.
Add bean sprouts and soy sauce.
Let simmer until done.

title: washington's surprise
directions: Stir cake mix and pie filling together.
This will be very thick.
Combine eggs, vanilla, oil and nuts.
Add to cake mix; blend well.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 1 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate. Beat milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and baking mix in blender on high speed 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese. Cover and blend on high speed 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set. Cool.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 12 or 14-inch pizza pan with aluminum foil.
Spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Press cookie dough evenly into pan.
Press fruit snacks into pizza in decorative design.
Bake 20 minutes or until cookie edges are golden brown. Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove cookie from pan; discard foil.
Decorate as desired with icing, sugar crystals and decors. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil
pasta
until
well
cooked (approximately 15 minutes). Drain
in colander and cool.
Add vegetables, dressing and spice. Keep in covered bowl in refrigerator.

title: butter baked chicken and gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dip chicken into 1/2 cup Pet milk. Then roll in self-rising flour.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan, then put chicken in, turn and bake with skin side down for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Pour over it a mixture of 3/4 cup Pet milk, cream of chicken soup and water.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Mix small can of peaches (drained) and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spoon over batter. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Marinate the meat for at least 4 to 6 days.
Make marinade with all spices and liquid except cream.
Brown the meat and bake it in the stove for 2 hours.
Strain the gravy.
Bind it with flour and heavy cream.
It may need more water during cooking.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix and shape into rolls.
Chill and slice.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in corn, kidney beans, soup, cheese, milk, onion and chili powder.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes.
Great with biscuits!

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix syrup and sugar. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and cornflakes. Stir real good and spoon drop on wax paper. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar; stir until mixed.
Cool.
Add eggs to shortening and sugar, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake in greased pan (10 x 15 x 1/2-inch) at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut when almost cool.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in oats, nuts and chips.
Dough will be thick.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Do not overcook.
Take out while barely set.
Cool on absorbent paper.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Put chicken in large pot and cover well with water.
Cook until tender.
Take chicken out of water and set aside to cool. Add to water, celery, carrots, onions and bouillon cube.
Cook until celery is tender.
Meanwhile, pick chicken off bones.
Add to mixture when it is cooked.
Put oleo and noodles in mixture; cook until the noodles are done.
Add more water if needed to make a 6-quart pot full.
Serve with salad and biscuit and enjoy the compliments.

title: ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add cream, butter, vanilla and salt and stir well.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in gallon glass container with loose cover at room temperature.
Stir 2 or 3 times the first day and once a day thereafter.
At the end of 2 weeks, the starter is ready to use for making your 30-day cake.

title: creamy chicken spread
directions: Put all ingredients into the food processor and process until chopped.
Use as a sandwich spread or on crackers.
This is great!

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Bring fruit to a boil.
Mix sugar, flour and milk and pour over butter in pan.
Pour hot fruit over this and bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around 10 green beans. Melt brown sugar, margarine and garlic powder in pan. Bring to a boil. Pour over all bundles. Bake 25 minutes at 300°. Then bake 5 more minutes at 400°. Serves 4.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Grease 8 x 10-inch baking dish with fat or oil.
Add mixture and bake at 500° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400°.
Bake 45 minutes or until crust is brown and crispy.

title: lamar's ice cream
directions: Blend milk, eggs, sugar and salt; cook in a double boiler until thoroughly hot.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Finish filling freezer with milk.
Freeze.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let set 1 hour before serving.

title: fruit cake (no bake)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Will be thick. Separate in small amounts and roll in wax paper. Store in refrigerator. Melt milk and marshmallows in double boiler.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine, Egg Beaters and vanilla. Add flour and mix until thoroughly blended.
Chill dough for 1 hour. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.

Press 4 to 5 chocolate chips into each dough ball. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. This will give you the satisfaction of a chocolate chip cookie without destroying your fat budget.
Providing you use good judgment and limit your intake, you can enjoy all the foods you are familiar with.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Clean, debone and skin chicken; cut each breast half into four pieces; pat dry.
Place vegetable oil, garlic and ginger in a medium skillet on medium heat; lightly brown chicken on all sides. Spoon off excess fat.
Add Mirin and brown sugar, cook until sugar is dissolved and turning chicken to coat.
Add soy sauce but do not stir.
Bring to a boil and let boil one minute, then continue turning chicken to coat.
When chicken is cooked through, remove skillet from heat.
Set chicken aside on a plate to cool, then shred.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Pour half and half into a large bowl.
Add pie filling mix. Beat with a wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and chopped candies.
Spoon into crust; top with chopped candies.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let thaw for 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican dish(microwave)
directions: First you take the seeds and you pop them.

title: citrus fizz
directions: Combine 1 part fruit juice to 3 parts 7-Up (i.e., 1/4 cup juice and 3/4 cup 7-Up).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl.
Place in a medium size casserole dish.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade pickled eggs
directions: Place cooked eggs in large jar.
Cover with vinegar completely.
Add spices.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate for at least one week.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Stir in cooked spaghetti.
In frying pan, brown both meats with chopped onion; drain.
Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam and then layer spaghetti mixture, sauce, meat and cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered; then bake 15 more minutes uncovered.
Let sit for 5 minutes before serving.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and green peppers in butter until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in the soup, mushrooms, pimentos and onions. Set aside.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Prepare mashed potatoes as directed, except omit butter and milk.
In a small bowl, blend cream cheese, milk, butter, egg and onion on low speed. Stir in potato mixture. Stir in grated cheese.
Pour into prepared casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer 1-Refried beans
Layer 2-Ripe avocados, lemon juice & salt, mixed together
Layer 3-Taco mix, sour cream & mayonnaise, mixed together
Layer 4-black olives
Layer 5-chopped onions Layer 6-chopped tomatoes
Layer 7-grated cheese

title: peanut clusters
directions: Put chips in microwave 2 to 3 minutes until glossy.
Mix in potato chips and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: date and nut balls
directions: Cook
first
5 ingredients 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add
the rice cereal and chopped nuts.
Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Stir sugar into fruit; set aside for 10 minutes.
Mix water and Sure-Jell; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil 1 minute, then stir Sure-Jell mixture into fruit mixture; stir for 3 minutes, constantly.
Fill containers immediately 1/2-inch from top.
Let stand at room temperature for a day or overnight, then freeze.

title: basic brownies
directions: In small bowl, at medium speed on mixer, beat together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla for about 1 minute, until light.
Add melted butter, beating until well blended.
Mix in flour and cocoa at low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch square dish.
Microwave at High 6 to 7 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 2 minutes.
When done, top looks dry and will spring back when touched.
Cut when cold.
Makes about 20 brownies.

title: grandma's ice creamwoodland park, colorado
directions: Warm milk to luke warm.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice firm, green tomatoes in slices, about a quarter or half-inch thick.
Dip each slice in corn meal to which you have added a generous amount of salt and a dash of sugar.
Fry in salad oil until brown; turn once during cooking.
One tomato makes 3 or 4 slices.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour over beans and add 1/2 can of onions.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put half of onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Dissolve flour in water.
Heat water.
Add salt, mustard and butter.
Add cheese.
Stir constantly until thick.
Pour into jars. Let cool, then refrigerate.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix ham, cheese and bread.
Beat eggs and milk and then pour over mixture.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick chunk pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil for five minutes.
Pack your pickle chunks into pint jars.
Pour the juice over and fill jars leaving 1/2
inch of space at top of jar.
Wash off the top of the jar and put lid and ring on jar.
Put into canner and cover jars with hot water.
Make sure they boil for five minutes.
Take jars out of canner and put on dry cloth to cool.
Makes about 10 pints.

title: swiss twist bread
directions: Combine 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast. Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes.
Work in balance of flour and knead to make a smooth, elastic dough.
(When you press your finger into the dough a slight indention remains.) Place in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth (wax paper between dough and cloth) and allow to rise to double in bulk.

title: blender quiche
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except cheese and meat in a blender.
Pour into
a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Press cheese and meat into the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let rest 10 minutes before cutting.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking soda, salt and sugar and sift again.
Combine milk, egg and shortening.
Add to flour mixture, stirring only enough to blend.
Turn into greased muffin tins.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening, white sugar, egg, brown sugar and persimmon pulp together.
Add flour, cinnamon, vanilla, raisins or dates, nutmeg, salt, baking powder and chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix.
Roll into ball or loaf and cover with parsley.

title: chicken picatta
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green onion in oil until tender. Remove from pan and set aside.
Skin and bone chicken breasts and pound flat.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into flour mixture.
Lightly brown chicken in butter 2 to 3 minutes per side. Add sauteed onion and garlic.
Over high heat, add the sherry, lemon juice and capers.
This should thicken to a nice gravy; if too thick, add broth or wine.
Serve breasts topped with lemon slices, sauce and chopped parsley.

title: citrus gazpacho grilled chicken
directions: Make the same recipe again, omitting the oil.
Heat to a boil on the range.
Remove and cool.
Reserve this mixture for the basting of the chicken when it is on the grill.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients.
In cheesecloth bag, add tea leaves, mint and cloves and put bag in mixture.
Cover and steep for 1 hour.
Strain and add hot water to dilute to taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pasta-chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients, except lettuce, tossing well.
Chill. Spoon into a lettuce lined bowl.
Yields 8 servings.

title: simple banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg.

Blend in bananas and lemon juice. Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream. Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes (until tester comes out clean).
Cool before slicing.

title: old fashion egg custard pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, corn meal and nutmeg.
Add butter.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add milk and flavoring last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple and juice.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs and flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup chocolate chips. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Immediately sprinkle with remaining chips.
Let stand 5 minutes and spread over top.

title: chicken pie
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch or 11 x 13-inch casserole dish, mix the soup with both cans of Veg-All (drain liquid from 1 can) and add the chicken.
Spread evenly.
In a separate bowl, combine Bisquick, milk and butter.
Pour batter over top.
Bake at 350° until batter is set (approximately 35 minutes).
Dot top with butter during the last few minutes for a nice, golden crust.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: To mayonnaise, add prepared mustard, dry mustard, vinegar, garlic salt, curry powder, grated onion and horseradish.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: molded avocado and pineapple salad
directions: Mash cream cheese and avocados; mix.
Add mayonnaise. Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 cup additional water and pineapple with juice.
Combine gelatin mixture with cheese and avocado mixture.
Mold in individual molds and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first three ingredients for 5 minutes, then add next three ingredients.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake in oven at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir well every 15 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Boil chicken and let cool.
Tear chicken into small strips. Put into pan and add taco mix and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cut up peppers and onion.
Saute in another pan until tender.
Heat shells in oven.
Spoon chicken into shells and top with pepper, onions and cheese.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Strain mixtures, discarding spices.
Gradually add fruit juice to hot mixture and heat thoroughly.
Garnish with orange slices if desired.
Yields 10 cups.

title: irish cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs and milk.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together, then gradually add raisins.
Bake one hour in greased Bundt pan.

title: oat-nut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Pour into thawed pie shell and bake 50 to 60 minutes, until top and crust are golden and a pick in center comes out clean but oily.
(May be jiggly in center.)
Cool on wire rack.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing, divided in half.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Stir in half of stuffing mix and other ingredients.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Spread other half of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Stir together sugar and cocoa.
Add milk; stir until boiling. Use cold water ball method for hardness test.
When done, beat in vanilla, butter and nuts, if wanted (black walnuts or pecans).

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain the liquid from the pickles.
Slice each pickle into chunks.
Put pickles back in jar.
Combine the rest of ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Pour hot mixture over the pickles in the jar.
Replace cover, cool and refrigerate.
Let stand 4 days to bring out flavor.

title: persimmon cookies by mary mcdowall
directions: Drop.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
I double it. (Double everything!)
I do not grind nuts and raisins.
I do chop up the nuts.
Good Luck!

title: cobblers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use any type of fruit.
Put into any kind of pan for a cobbler.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: indian corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add cheese and corn.
Stir in about 3/4 of the bacon.
Turn mixture into an ungreased baking dish; sprinkle remaining bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix together.
Spread in glass baking dish (9 x 13-inch). Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Cover with crushed potato chips (large bag).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Cook the above ingredients to 260 degrees or soft crack stage.
Pour over 2 quarts salted popcorn.
Mix thoroughly and mold into balls.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thick.
Let cool completely and fold in whipped cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: topsy turvey salad
directions: Mix cheese, marshmallows, pineapple and Cool Whip together. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Let set and serve.

title: chocolate cheese bars
directions: Melt chocolate pieces, cream cheese and evaporated milk.
Add nuts and vanilla; set aside.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Pour batter into lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole with praline topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring to form a streusel.
Set aside.
Place potatoes in a Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 min. or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash in a large bowl.
Stir in 1 cup streusel, sugar, vanilla, egg white and milk.
Spoon into a 2 qt. casserole coated with cooking spray and top with remaining streusel.
Bake at 350° for 45 min.
Serves 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well and chill dough.
Make balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press on cookie ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in pot; bring to a boil. Boil 6 minutes. In a large bowl, put semi-sweet and German sweet chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts. Pour the boiling syrup over the chips. Stir until well mixed. Pour into buttered pans and cool. Cut into squares.

title: good apple crisp
directions: Mix with fork until crumbly the first 5 ingredients.
Slice apples in long dish and sprinkle mixture over them.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven until apples are tender. This is also great with peaches.

title: mushroom sandwiches
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter. Blend in flour, salt and Accent. Stir in cream and cook until thick. Add lemon juice and chives. Blend well. Cut crust off bread and roll until thin, using rolling pin.
Spread with sauce and roll up (jelly roll fashion). Freeze on cookie sheet in single layers.
Keep frozen until ready to use.

title: meme's bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt oleo in Bundt pan.
You must use a Bundt pan.
Stand rolls of biscuits in pan on sides.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.
Invert on platter.
Makes a beautiful loaf of pull apart bread.

title: e-z lasagna
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, salt, pepper and oregano in a large bowl, stir well.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place 1/2 of noodles over sauce, 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with noodles, sauce and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around edges, cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: summer squash skillet
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Add squash and tomatoes.
Cook over low heat just until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters, slice thin, discard white heart. Place in 20-quart pot with metal place in bottom to prevent burning; add more cabbage as it cooks until it all fits in pot. Add water, simmer for 2 hours without lid.
Stir occasionally. Put lid on and cook for another hour.
Add jelly, vinegar and caraway seed; continue simmering for one more hour.
Turn off and let sit overnight.
Put into jars and refrigerate.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add condensed milk, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Stir in mashed peaches and pour into a 1 1/2-gallon ice cream freezer.
Fill freezer to full line with whole milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: praline cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Add uncooked rice.
Stir in soup and water.
Mix in vegetables.
Place pieces of chicken on top of rice mixture and bake at 350° for about an hour or until chicken is done and rice is not soupy.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix and pour into skillet or griddle.
Fry; turn when bubbles and brown.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in large bowl.
Mix oil and seasonings.
Pour over crackers and toss several times over the next hour.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan.
Beat brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Stir in baking mix and nuts until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture in pan and bake 12 minutes.

title: ruth stovall's olive surprises
directions: Have butter and cheese at room temperature.
Blend these together with fingertips.
Add flour, gradually blending well.
Add garlic salt and Tabasco and mix well.
Break off small bits and flatten in palm of hand.
Use only enough dough to wrap completely around olives.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overcook.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all the mixture, except the pecans.
Work into a ball; roll into the chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: stripping furniture recipe
directions: Thin dry starch with cold water.
Add enough boiling water to make 1 quart.
Add Climatine.
Use when hot.
Brush on thick, let dry and pour hot water over.
Best to do outside.

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute meat lightly.
Add seasoning, sauce and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Add tortilla chips.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 400°.

title: fudge-cuts
directions: Start heating oven to 400°.
Grease two 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans. In a double boiler, melt chocolate and shortening; remove from water.
Add sugar, eggs, then flour, salt and vanilla.
Stir well. Pour into pans.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 12 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 32 (2-inch) squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugars and eggs together. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine instant breakfast drink, sugar, instant tea, spices and salt.
Store in tightly covered jar.

title: confetti taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
If made ahead of time, save tomato and chips until right before serving, then toss dressing in.

title: kikko burgers
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Shape into 4 to 6 patties.
Broil or grill to desired doneness, brushing lightly with additional Kikkoman.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, softened butter and flour together.
Scoop out small amount of dough, about the size of a walnut, and place in mini-muffin pan.
Press dough evenly around sides and bottom, leaving a pocket for the filling.

title: "steak" soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add margarine and flour.
Stir and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remainder of ingredients and stir.
Simmer until vegetables are tender for approximately 2 hours.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add pork chops and brown quickly on both sides.
Remove chops and drain all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Cook onion and green pepper until soft.
Ad tomato sauce, water, sugar and seasonings.
Heat to boiling and cook for 5 minutes.

Arrange potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place pork chops on top of potatoes and pour sauce over all. Cover casserole with lid or foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: great brownies
directions: Flour and grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 1 package of cake mix with 3/4 cup melted butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup nuts.
Stir and put 1/2 of dough into pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Then combine 1/3 cup evaporated milk with 1 package caramels and melt together over low heat.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips, then spread remaining 1/2 dough over caramel mixture.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: In saucepan, combine vinegar, water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil and boil for one minute.
Place vegetables in a salad bowl. Pour dressing (hot) over vegetables and refrigerate several hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8, 30 calories each.

title: cannoli(cheese filled pastry; italy)
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Rub the shortening into the dry ingredients until it resembles a fine meal.
Beat the eggs, orange flavoring and water together on high speed.
Add this to the meal like mixture and mix together.
Even though it seems dry, do not add more liquid.
Turn this out onto a floured board and knead until a smooth ball is formed.
Let the dough rest about a half hour, then roll into a thin sheet of dough, about 1/8 of an inch thick.
Cut into strips the size of a shell you desire.
Wrap around a metal or wood form and seal edges together with water. Fry in deep hot 360° fat until brown.
Cool and fill with whipped Ricotta cream, sweetened to taste and flavored with cinnamon and vanilla.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: blueberry butter
directions: Select the best man you
can
find, and brush him carefully to rid him of	all indifference.
Be careful not to beat him as you would an egg,
for	beating will make him tough and apt to froth at the
mouth.
Lift
him
gently
into
the home preserving kettle, and tie
him with strong bonds of affection which are not easily broken.
Do not sear him with sarcasm, as that causes spitting
and
sputtering,	which
may
ultimately result in spontaneous
combustion.
Scramble when difficulties arise.
Do not soak him
in liquor either as excessive alcohol will make him mushy and
spongy
with your friends, and stewed husbands
have never been popular.
It
is
best
to
let	him simmer tenderly at will;
to blend tactfully with dressing and seasonings.
Stuff him one
hour
before
taking out or before asking a favor of him.
A little caress will often add to his tenderness.
Flavor him with the oil of happiness, an ounce of understanding, and bushel of laughter and fun.
Should he seem weak or troubled with
feminine infatuation, smother him with onions and garlic, and treble your charms.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling liquid (the reserved pineapple juice and water).
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add evaporated milk and beat well.
Slowly stir milk mixture into gelatin.
Stir in rind and orange juice.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Pour into 6 cup mold which has been lightly brushed with oil.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: original green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: mexican okra
directions: Brown beef and onion in large, heavy skillet.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and okra.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until okra is tender.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion over medium heat; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.

title: clay
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all of the ingredients.
Over medium heat, cook the mixture for 4 to 5 minutes, or until it thickens and pulls away from the sides of the pan.
With a spoon, transfer the clay to a pie tin.
Cover with a damp cloth and allow to cool.
On a flat surface covered with waxed paper, knead the clay 2 minutes.
Sculpt as desired, then allow to dry overnight on a piece of waxed paper.
Paint with acrylic colors and shellac. Store any remaining clay in a resealable bag.

title: grandma's lemon delight
directions: Mix together.
Press into 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: colonial pot roast
directions: Put all together and cook in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours on high.

title: egg drop soup (aka bird drop soup)
directions: Bring all ingredients except eggs to a boil. Add eggs. Season with soy sauce.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in mayonnaise. Stir until dissolved. Add Pet milk and other ingredients.
Pour into oblong cake pan. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini,
onions and green and red peppers.
Add salt. Set
overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring
to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes,
stirring	occasionally.
Pour into hot jars. Seal and process for 5 minutes.

title: oven chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten each chicken breast half to 1/4-inch thickness between waxed paper.
Divide ham and Swiss cheese among chicken breasts. Roll each chicken breast up and secure with a wooden pick.
Mix corn flakes, parsley and paprika.
Dip chicken into buttermilk. Coat evenly with corn flake mixture.
Place chicken, seam sides down, in greased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake, uncovered, in 425° oven for 35 minutes; remove wooden picks.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring to a boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over packed cucumbers.
For each quart of packed cucumbers, add 1 big piece of fresh dill, 1 small hot pepper and 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon garlic. The smaller the cucumber, the better the pickle.
Serve cold.

title: grandma's sloppy joes
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt and pepper in a large skillet.
Cook until meat is lightly browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Stir in soup, catsup and mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
In skillet, melt oleo; add broccoli and chopped onion.
Heat until broccoli separates. Mix Cheez Whiz and Pet milk.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings on top of casserole and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: dot's wowie cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; blend well.
Add rest of ingredients and blend until smooth.
It is not necessary to grease the pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or 20 to 25 minutes for cupcakes. Makes 12 cupcakes or 1 layer.
This recipe is great for heart patients - low cholesterol.

title: chocolate covered sandwiches
directions: Melt 2 to 3 cubes of white chocolate candy in the microwave. Dip the peanut butter sandwiches in chocolate.
Lay them on wax paper to cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Remove any fat.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in frying pan.
Add meat; cook and stir until brown. Remove meat from pan; set aside.
Cook onion and mushrooms in same pan until tender.
Return meat to pan.
Mix the broth, mustard and catsup; pour over meat.
Cover; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Make paste of flour and water; stir into pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add yogurt or sour cream; do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: eggs with mayonnaise and shrimp
directions: Halve eggs and place in middle of serving dish.
Remove any shells or veins in shrimp.
Arrange in circle around eggs.
Add cream to mayonnaise; stir until well blended.
Pour over eggs and top with dill sprig.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix everything together and store in an airtight container. Use 1/3 cup of mix with enough hot water to fill a mug.
Makes a lot but it will all be gone when winter's over!

title: german sweet sour cabbage
directions: Quarter head of cabbage; chop coarsely, cutting out stem.
Put fat in frypan.
Saute onion in fat.
Put cabbage and cut apple in. Put sugar, vinegar, salt, red wine and sauteed onion in.
Put cinnamon stick in ingredients.
Cook in boiling pan.
Steam rather than boil.
Stir ingredients well and cook until done.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain, discarding fruit and cinnamon sticks. Serve hot.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: chunky beef over rice
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, broccoli and Worcestershire sauce over medium heat.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
5 minutes.

title: evelyn's pickle relish
directions: Place in a cheesecloth bag and add to the mixture.
Boil all ingredients together for 30 minutes.
Remove the bag of spices. Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Roll into patties and fry until brown or cook on grill.

title: tricia's fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; serve chilled.

title: burger bundles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix meat, soup mix, egg, pepper, water and bread crumbs.
Press onto bottom of 15 x 10-inch baking pan. Prick meat mixture with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or to desired doneness.
Drain.

title: joan's zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
If doubling recipe, pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: vegetable-egg-cheese scramble
directions: Beat the eggs lightly in a bowl, blending in the milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cut the cream cheese into small pieces and add to the mixture along with the vegetables and cheese.
Melt
the margarine in a skillet.
Pour in the egg mixture and cook over a low heat.
Gently lift eggs from the bottom occasionally to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath. Serve when firm but still moist. Garnish with the chives.
Serves 5 to 6 people.
This can also be cooked in an omelette pan.

title: super pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in flour alternately with combined milk and extracts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 20 minutes.

title: lil hot dogies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut hot dogs lengthwise about three-fourths through.
Fill each with 1 tablespoon relish; set aside.
In medium bowl combine biscuit mix, cornmeal, paprika and mustard.
In 1-cup measure beat egg slightly with fork, add enough milk to make 3/4 cup.
Make well in center of dry ingredients.
Add milk mixture, all at once, stirring just to blend.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead 12 to 15 times.
Roll out into 12-inch square.
With floured sharp knife cut 9 squares (about 4 inches each).
Wrap a square around each frank, leaving ends exposed.
Place, seam side down, on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with sugar and vinegar.
Add onion, seasoning and mayonnaise; toss to mix.
Carefully fold eggs in. Chill; garnish with parsley and cherry tomatoes or tomato wedges and deviled egg.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook together hamburger, onion and pepper (until not red). Mix all together, then put all in casserole and cover with foil. Bake one hour at 350°.
Take foil off; put grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: luscious butterscotch yams
directions: Place yams in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, mix remaining ingredients.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over yams. Bake, basting often, 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: marble marshmallow brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan.
In small heavy saucepan over very low heat, stir butter and unsweetened chocolate until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat, cool.

title: cream cheese ball dessert
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and pudding.
Fold in fruit cocktail.
Shape into a roll or ball and roll in nuts.
Pecans are best, but any kind can be used.
Chill.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter or margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save half.
Mix 1 3/4 cup milk into 2 packages pudding.
Into this, mix 1 quart ice cream.
Fold in Cool Whip. Mix well and pour into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate covered overnight.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and milk for 90 seconds.
Remove from microwave.
Quickly stir and mix in nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a Saran Wrap-covered pan.

title: yummy cheese spread
directions: Early in the day, mix all ingredients.
Chill all day.
Remove from refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears and vegetables together.
Put in pan and add mustard, vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Bring to boil, stirring often, and cook 2-3 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: sweet and tangy chicken
directions: Put chicken in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Wet bread with water.
Mix until mushy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and clean cranberries and place in a large pan.
Add water to cranberries and cook for 5 minutes, then add sugar and continue to cook over a medium heat until all the berries have popped. (Around 1/2 hour).
Remove from heat and add Jello, apples, nuts, oranges and celery, making sure mixture is stirred well.
Pour into pans and place in refrigerator until mixture is jelled, best if it sets for at least 24 hours in the refrigerator. Cut and serve.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package; drain. Rinse with cold water, drain and lay flat on paper towels in single layer until needed.
Meanwhile, mix together ricotta cheese, cream cheese, onion, basil, and garlic stir in vegetables.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand.
Cream sugars and margarine.
Beat eggs into mix.
Add vanilla and softened oatmeal. Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add to other mixture and blend.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Leave in pan and pour icing over warm cake.

title: mama sarah's own macaroni elbow casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
In buttered casserole, make layers of macaroni, hamburger, tomatoes, celery, onion and cheese.
Repeat layers and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: arthur treacher style fish
directions: Soak fish in just enough buttermilk to cover; refrigerate in covered container with 1 lemon sliced over it for 2 hours to remove fishy taste.
Heat oil in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Drain off milk.
Cut fillets in halves (make triangle shapes). Dredge in dry pancake mix.

title: easy meat and tater casserole
directions: Line bottom and sides of 11 x 13-inch baking dish with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fry and drain ground beef. Layer onto tots, beef, broccoli, tomatoes and 1/2 can onions.
In a bowl mix together soup, milk, pepper, garlic and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour mixture over top of other ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until done (not soupy).
Remove from oven and top with remaining onions and cheese.
Return to oven for about 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions.
Add mushroom soup and taco sauce. Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Line pan with tortilla chips. Cover with beef mixture; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste with coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk and vanilla.
Alternately add soda and vinegar.
Blend.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: double cheese macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water.
(I add a little oil to my water.)
Drain.
Add butter, milk and Velveeta.
When Velveeta is melted, place in bowl and spread Cheddar cheese on top.
Heat in microwave on High for approximately 1 minute or until Cheddar cheese is melted on top.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and Cool Whip.
Chill and enjoy!
Serves 6.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease and flour large pound cake pan. Blend softened butter, Philadelphia cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Next, add sifted flour with salt.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
If mix becomes too thick, you can add milk, a tablespoon at a time, until desired consistency is obtained.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Sometimes what I'll do at the end of the scheduled baking time, if the cake still isn't done, reduce the heat to 325° and continue to bake until done.
Allow to cool about 10 minutes before you remove cake from pan.

title: tropical fruit cooler
directions: Add hot water to jello; dissolve.
Add cold water, fruit juice and sugar; stir well.
Just before serving, add whipped bananas and strawberries.
May be garnished with sliced bananas or sherbet.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Do not pull apart. Mash together.
Bake 11 minutes or as directed.
Cool.
Mix dressing, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Mash into cream cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Chill (overnight preferred).
Remove from refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: tabouli
directions: Soak bulgur wheat in 1 3/4 cups of water.
It should be soaked a couple of hours or more.
If you want to speed up the process, soak in hot water.
Wash parsley; drain well and let dry in a towel.
Cut off the stems.
Mince in a food processor or by hand. Cut up tomatoes in fairly small bits.
Cut onions fine.
Use either fresh or bottled lemon juice.
Mix all ingredients.
Add salt to taste.
Tastes really good if left sitting in the refrigerator for several hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: stir-fry ala jeane
directions: Put oil in wok and heat to high.
Add garlic and your choice of meat.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes, then drain on paper towel.
In remaining juice, stir-fry veggies by density until crisp.
You don't want soggy veggies.
Mix soy sauce with cornstarch and grated ginger.
Add meat to veggies.
Make hole in center of mixture.
Add sauce and let set a minute on high, then stir all together.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Blend first four ingredients.
Add flour and blend.
Add buttermilk, and maple flavoring.
Blend.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan. Turn out on serving plate, poke holes on top with straw while warm.
Spoon glaze over top.

title: creamy reception punch
directions: Spoon vanilla ice cream by tablespoons into a large punch bowl.
Add orange juice and lemon juice, stirring to muddle ice cream.
Slowly pour in lemon-lime beverage; stir gently to mix. Makes 36 (4 ounce) servings.

title: lemon angel cake
directions: Beat egg whites until light and stiff.
Add the sugar gradually to form a meringue.
Stop beating and fold in the flour and cream of tartar sifted together.
Add lemon and turn into ungreased angel food cake tin in an oven at a temperature of 325°.
When baked, turn over on an icing frame to cool.
When cold, remove from the form and ice all over with a lemon icing.

title: beef strudel
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in oil.
Pour package of egg noodles (uncooked) over top of hamburg/onion mixture.
Mix all the other ingredients together.
Pour this mixture over the noodles.
Cook for 1/2 to 3/4 of an hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with a green salad.

title: salmon on the grill
directions: Double aluminum foil and punch holes in it.
Place fish on foil.
Season fish with herbs, seasoning salt and lemon pepper. Spread mayonnaise on top of fish.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes in closed grill.

title: fruit sauce
directions: ...is still a SECRET!!

title: citrus's crab coleslaw
directions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
Remove 6 large green outer leaves of the cabbage.
Plunge into water about 3 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Pat dry.
Quarter and core cabbage and shred 1 packed cup.
Place in a medium bowl.
In a medium bowl, whisk together mayonnaise and vinegar until smooth.
Stir in the tarragon, ketchup, mustard, hot sauce, curry powder and pepper; add cabbage and toss.
Remove cores of the 6 large leaves; lay on flat surface with the stem ends facing you.
Fill each one with 1/4 cup of the crab mixture.
Roll up.
Cut each one into 4 pieces. Garnish with bell peppers.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Slowly cook the first four ingredients for 15 minutes.
Add boiled eggs and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Let stand in a covered container until cooled.
Then refrigerate.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cut up chicken and mix with soup, sour cream and water.
Pour into casserole dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch). Melt margarine.
Crush crackers and toss with margarine.
Cover casserole with Cheddar cheese, then with crackers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: philadelphia cream cheese ball
directions: Soften	cheese	and
combine with Worcestershire sauce, Accent,
onion
and 1 package of beef.
Roll ball in remaining beef and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: pineapple shortcake
directions: Bake the first 6 ingredients in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Boil next 3 ingredients slowly for 10 minutes, then add nuts and coconut.
Spread over cake while hot.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, ham and onion in a greased 1-quart casserole; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over potato mixture.
Stir gently to mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Recipe serves 2.
It can be doubled or tripled for family.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil and garlic until tender (not browned) over medium low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thickened.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: prune lunch box cake
directions: Cook prunes in water to cover; simmer prunes for 5 minutes. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add prune mixture and remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly 1 minute.
Pour into greased and floured pan (8 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: jeremiah sweeny's broccoli soup
