directions: Combine all soups, thawed broccoli, milk and water.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Add stick of margarine and season with celery salt and onion flakes to taste.
Add more liquid if you prefer a thinner soup.

title: vegetables with garlic and ginger sauce
directions: Wash all vegetables.
Chop ends off beans, slice pepper lengthwise, cut scallions in 2-inch lengths.
Finely chop garlic and ginger and place in saucepan.
Add tamari and vinegar.
Heat the oil in frying pan until hot.
Add vegetables.
Cover and fry, shaking from time to time.
Bring garlic and ginger to a boil and cook 30 seconds only.
When vegetables are to liking, add sauce, put lid on pan and shake.
Remove to platter and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix water and Eagle Brand milk.
Add instant pudding and chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break cake into pieces.
Layer cake, pudding and strawberries in a large bowl, ending with pudding.
Decorate with strawberries.
Pudding mix may also be used with vanilla wafers and bananas for banana pudding.

title: tamales
directions: Combine
beef,
pork,
vinegar,
teaspoon
salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and
water in a large pot; cover and cook over low heat about
hours or until meat is tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Shred
meat
with a fork.
Cover dried corn husks with hot
water;
let
stand
1 to 2 hours or until softened.
Drain
well and pat with paper towels to remove excess water.
(If husks
are
too
narrow, overlap 2 husks to make a wide one; if
husks are too wide, tear off one side.) Use an 8 x 8-inch square
of
foil
for each tamale if dried corn husks are not
available.
Saute
garlic
and cumin seed in 3 tablespoons shortening
for
minutes.
Add
shredded meat, 1 cup reserved broth,
tablespoon
chili
powder, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 30 minutes,
stirring occasionally.

title: buttermilk pie(aunt tera's)
directions: Melt butter and mix with eggs and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir in 2 teaspoons lemon and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake in crust at 350° until it sets.

title: zippy zucchini skillet
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; saute zucchini and onion 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated. Stir in cheese.
Yield:
6 servings.
(Make day before, enhances flavor.)

title: cheese carrots
directions: Cook carrots with salt and sugar until tender.
Drain.
Add cream, butter and layer with cheese.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is fully melted.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello and Kool-Aid in boiling water.
Stir in cold water until mixed.
Freeze in tray.

title: crunchy tuna patties
directions: In a medium bowl, combine tuna, egg, salad dressing, 2 tablespoons of the crushed potato chips and pepper until well blended.
Shape into 4 patties.
Place remaining crushed chips on a plate.
Coat both sides of each of the patties with crushed chips.
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add patties and cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side, until cooked through and golden.

title: pineapple fluff pudding
directions: Drain pineapple.
Prepare both pudding mixes minus 1/2 cup of the milk.
Prepare both packages of Dream Whip minus 1/2 cup milk. Add pineapple, coconut and nuts to pudding mix, mix well. Carefully add Dream Whip.
Can use this as a pie when put in a graham cracker crust.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil together the sugar, butter and milk for six minutes. Pour remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat until chocolate is melted and mixture has thickened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in 9-inch square pan. Let stand a few hours before cutting.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Squeeze all water out of spinach.
In large bowl, mix cottage cheese, 2 1/2 cups Mozzarella, egg, spinach, salt, oregano, pepper and mushrooms.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, layer 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, 3 to 4 lasagne noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture.
Again layer 3 to 4 noodles, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, 1/2 cheese mixture, 3 to 4 noodles and remaining spaghetti sauce.
Top with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water/wine mixture around edges.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: applesauce cake(improves with age)
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Mix spices, soda and salt with flour.
Add raisins and currants and add to creamed mixture. Stir in applesauce.
Pour into greased and flour dusted loaf pan (6 x 10-inch). Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Turn out of pan. Frost with favorite icing and pecans.
Decorate with tinted sugar.

title: chicken pie
directions: Debone boiled chicken.
Save broth.
Place in lasagna dish. Mix vegetables with chicken.
Place pats of butter on chicken mixture.
Mix cream of chicken soup, evaporated milk and 2 cups chicken broth.
Pour over mixture.
Mix remaining broth with flour.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef and vegetable soup
directions: In large soup pot, brown ground beef with onion.
Then add all of the rest of the vegetables and water with juice and all.
Boil for about 1 hour on medium heat.

title: "willie nilly" chili pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions, using half the suggested amount of water.
Place in 9-inch pie pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Place several pats of margarine in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces in bottom of pan.
In medium size bowl, mix soups, rice and water.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs, well beaten.
Sift flour, salt and soda 3 times.
Mix cocoa, food coloring and vinegar together. Add eggs to sugar mixture and beat well.
Add dry mixture, milk and vanilla alternately.
Beat until blended.
Bake in 2 or 3 layers in greased and floured pans at 330° or 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (about 30 to 40 minutes). Frost with Red Velvet Frosting when cool.

title: basque cake(gateau basque)
directions: Put the flour in a large bowl.
Make a hole in middle and place sugar, salt, butter, egg yolks, baking powder and lemon peel into the hole.
Use your hands to work everything together into a dough.

title: karin's tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix noodles, tuna, soup and peas.
Add mayonnaise and milk to make moist.
Salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Chop vegetables and saute in oil until soft.
Put water in a large saucepan.
Place sausages in water and boil them until no longer pink.
Reserve water.
Remove sausage and place in skillet with vegetables.
Add tomato sauce.
Add all the spices and bring the sauce to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Leave butter and eggs out night before. Put milk out in the morning so it will be room temperature. Cream sugar and butter until creamy. Add 1 egg at a time. Divide milk and pour into three proportions for adding to mixture. Beat well. Add flavoring. Pour into 10-inch tube pan, well-greased and floured. Pour in cake batter and knock down so no bubbles will be in pan. Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes. You can tell when the sides come loose from pan.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook ham in hot oil until lightly browned.
Add next 8 ingredients and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, lemon pieces and shrimp.
Simmer slowly, uncovered, tossing often until shrimp are pink (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove bay leaves and lemon.
Mix with freshly steamed rice; check seasonings and heat well.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Boil water and set aside to cool just a bit.
Pour in carefully the three supplements and mix very well.
Mixture will thicken by the last supplement.
Mix in 1/2 of package of cheese. Pour 1/2 of soup mixture into a flat glass dish.
Place drained asparagus spears on top of mixture.
Sprinkle diced mushrooms on top of asparagus followed by 1/4 of cheese on top of mushrooms. Pour remainder of soup mixture as top layer over vegetables. Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top of soup.
Sprinkle top with finely ground Melba toast.
Bake at 350° in oven about 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: cold day chili
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Assemble in layers as follows:

title: creole string beans
directions: Wash beans.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add beans and enough water to keep from burning.
Cover; cook slowly (stir occasionally) until tender.
Season to taste.
Peel potatoes; place on top of beans.
Steam until tender.
If you desire, place a slice or two of onion on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip, almond extract and yogurt in serving bowl. Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with fruit.

title: cottage meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine ketchup, tomato juice, salt, black and red peppers, eggs, bread crumbs, onions and mustard.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add ground beef.
Mix gently but thoroughly. Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil.
Press in the beef mixture. In a separate bowl, combine the topping ingredients, mixing well. Spread topping over the meat loaf.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Drain off fat.
Rest meat loaf 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with fresh herbs, if desired.
Good served with spinach salad, mashed potatoes and buttered broccoli.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown the ground chuck, celery, onion and green pepper.
Drain grease.
Add the seasonings and remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns or use as hot dog sauce.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine and mix well. Store in airtight container. Use 2 to 3 teaspoons for each cup of water. Different coffee creamers may be used.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Mix oil and onion soup mix in a large bowl. Peel and cut potatoes in potato chip slices. Put potatoes in bowl with mixture of oil and onion soup mix and stir until all potatoes are basted well. Pour potatoes along with remaining oil mixture into a baking dish lined with aluminum foil. Cover the potatoes with aluminum foil. Bake for 1 hour. Take out of oven and cover top with cheese; re-cover with aluminum foil and let sit until cheese melts. Now you're ready to eat!

title: chili
directions: Stir and saute the beef and onions until well done; drain. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan; add 1-inch water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside.
In the same pan, combine butter, brown sugar and salad dressing.
Mix until blended; add carrots.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes or until glazed.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: individual cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese; blend in sugar until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla. Line muffin tins with cupcake liners. Place one cookie in each liner, flat side down. Put about 2 tablespoons cream cheese mixture on each cookie. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the potatoes and eggs; mix well.
Mix syrup, milk, salt and vanilla and add to the potato mixture.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with the pie crust.
Put filling in pan and bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Bring to boil, then simmer, uncovered, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Makes 12 servings.

title: savory chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat, add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat, mix in the cereal until well coated.
Using a buttered spatula or wax paper, press into a 13x9 pan coated with cooking spray.
Makes about 24 squares.

title: cran-apple mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in cranberry sauce.
Add applesauce and wine. Chill until partially set.
Fold in nuts. Pour into mold or an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 6 to 8 hours. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sour kraut
directions: Chop cabbage and fill quart jar leaving 1-inch head space.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to each jar.
Pour boiling water over cabbage leaving 1-inch head space.
Seal at once.
Place jars in a dark cool place and let work for 6 weeks before using.

title: chew bars
directions: Mix as you would any cake.
Add ingredients in order as listed, adding melted oleo last.
Put in a greased and floured Pyrex dish about 13 1/2 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut immediately into bar shapes.
Do not ice.

title: haystack-em
directions: Drain beans.
Put on plate either corn chips or tortillas, then beans and pile up some of each ingredient on beans as you like. Very good.

title: apricot-glazed sweet potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Cut apricots into quarters.
In 2-quart pan, combine potatoes, apricots and water.
Cover and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender, maybe 15 minutes.
Add preserves.
Cook, uncovered, until potatoes are glazed and water is gone.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, be careful not to overcook.
Crumble sausage into large skillet; cook about 10 minutes.
Pour off some of the fat.
Stir in onion, pepper, garlic; saute for 5 minutes or until onion is soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Good served with salad and crusty bread.

title: pig licking cake
directions: Combine.
Bake at 325° according to directions on cake mix box.

title: lemon rice
directions: Heat butter; saute onion and carrots.
Add rice.
Do not brown rice or vegetables.
Add stock, juice and zest.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 18 to 20 minutes.

title: luscious lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, stir together 2 cups flour and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Cut the margarine into the mixture until it is crumbly.

title: bohemian steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
In deep pot, layer meat and onion.
Mix 1/2 water, beer, gravy, salt, pepper and garlic. Mix well.
Pour over meat and onion.
Simmer for about 75 to 85 minutes.
Stir together 1/4 cup of water and flour gradually.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Cover, uncovered, until thickened.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage; boil until tender and drain.
Saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add undiluted soup.
Mix well. Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer to a 2-quart baking dish. Melt remaining butter; stir bread crumbs into butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Leave cake in pan.
Bring to a boil in a saucepan the sugar, milk and coconut. Punch holes in cake with toothpick or fork and pour hot mixture over cake.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
When cake is cool, spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of coconut over top of Cool Whip.

title: sarah's seven layer dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix. Combine avocados and lemon juice.
In a large casserole or baking dish, 10 1/2 x 14 3/4-inch, layer ingredients in following order: refried beans, avocado mix, sour cream mix, tomatoes, cheeses, onions and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; set aside. Mix butter and sugar. Add eggs, raisins and sour cream; stir. Stir in dry ingredients. Batter will be stiff.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until top is golden brown. Wrap and slice bread the next day. Also freezes well.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Stir flour mixture gradually into creamed mixture one-third at a time.
Roll dough into balls the size of small walnuts.
In a custard cup, mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll balls in the mixture.
Place about 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly brown, but still soft.
(These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.)
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: quick pumpkin pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and milk.
Stir until thickened.
Then add pumpkin, Cool Whip, pumpkin pie spice and sugar.
Mix well and put in baked pie crust or graham cracker crust.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine first 6 ingredients and form into 40 bite-size meatballs, using a full teaspoon of ground beef mixture for each meatball. Place meatballs on a flat baking pan and cook for approximately 20 minutes, turning meatballs after about 10 minutes. Drain off excess fat and put meatballs into crock-pot. Add barbecue sauce and grape jelly. Heat, stirring occasionally, until jelly is melted. Simmer, about 15 minutes, until sauce has thickened, basting occasionally. Makes 40 appetizers (3/4 cup of sauce).

title: hot lemon drink
directions: Mix all ingredients together (best if mixed by hand).
Store in sealed plastic container.
Use 2 teaspoons of mixture per coffee mug; add boiling water.
This is an excellent drink for cold or flu sufferers.

title: quick veggie chili con queso
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine tomatoes, undrained pinto and kidney beans, drained garbanzo beans and hominy, tomato paste, undrained chili peppers, onions, zucchini, chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, sugar and salt to taste.
If desired, heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Serve with sour cream and garnish with cilantro, if desired.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the beef, 1/3 cup of sauce and remaining ingredients.
Spread in an ungreased loaf pan.
Spread remaining tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: egg bread
directions: Heat milk until bubbles
form
around edge of pan.
Add sugar, margarine and
raisins.
Cool
to	lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over water in
large
bowl.
Stir
until dissolved.
Add eggs and mix. Gradually add
flour
a
little at a time.	Mix with hands.
Place on board and knead until smooth, 5 minutes. Place in bowl and let rise until double.	Pound it down twice. Divide in half.
Roll out and place seam side down in 2 bread pans, brush with a little melted margarine on top of bread and let rise a little over
top. Bake
in
a
oven about 35 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: In large bowl stir together sweet potato, corn syrup, milk, cinnamon, ginger, salt, pecans and eggs.
Melt margarine in heavy 10-inch ovenproof skillet, preferrably black iron.
Pour in potato mixture; stir to mix.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring twice during baking.
Cool.
Spoon into dessert dishes and serve with whipped topping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: clam crisps
directions: Saute onions in butter for 2 to 3 minutes; remove from heat. Blend in flour, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder, then stir in the clams and clam liquid.
Cook over low heat until it thickens, about 1 minute.
Cool and spread mixture on bread and roll up.
At this point, they can be frozen on cookie sheets and stored in freezer paper or plastic bags.
When ready to use, roll in melted butter and place on cookie sheets.
Bake in a 425° oven until toasted.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given in very large bowl. (I beat with mixer, sugars, oil and eggs.)
Mix soda, baking powder, salt and flour in separate bowl, then add to first mixture; mix well.
Add oatmeal, coconut and corn flakes; mix well.
Add chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 14 dozen.

title: hoppin john
directions: Saute sausage and onions until onions are soft and sausage brown.
Combine black-eyed peas, sausage mixture and rice, then heat.
Serves 8.

title: sugarless oatmeal fruit cookies
directions: Sift together flour and soda; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, over medium-high heat, bring water, dates, apples and raisins to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add oleo and stir until melted.

title: chicken with vegetables(from italy)
directions: Place olive oil, butter, chicken and onion in a skillet. Saute until chicken is done.
Stir frequently. Cook carrots in a saucepan until done.
Add the peas and carrots. Cook for 5 minutes. Add the stock and water; stir. Bring to a boil and add rice.
Cook for about 20 minutes or until the rice is tender.
Add salt, pepper and cheese; mix well.
Serve hot.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Crumble some cheese on top.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, oil, eggs and enough water to 1 tablespoon rum flavoring to make 1 cup.
Mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Put nuts in bottom of pan and pour in batter. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Immediately pour on glaze. Leave in pan 30 minutes.
Then turn upside down, nuts being on top onto cake plate.

title: low-cholesterol oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then add egg whites.
Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add 1 cup dry ingredients at a time to creamed mixture, alternating with sour milk.
Batter will very stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Do not overbake.

title: bread starter and bread
directions: Mix ingredients in a glass jar or container.
Cover loosely and let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Put in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash in salted boiling water until very tender; drain well.
Completely mash squash and add onion, cheese, corn meal, flour and egg.
Mix until blended and the consistency of hush puppies or croquettes.
More meal may be needed, but do not get mixture stiff.
Fry in medium-hot vegetable oil until cooked through and browned.
Drain well on paper towel.
This mixture can be made and refrigerated, then cooked anytime within 3 days.

title: pioneers johnny cake
directions: Sift first five ingredients together (sifting several times makes it better).
Beat eggs into milk and water and add butter. Stir liquid into dry mixture; add more liquid if needed.
Bake in muffin pans or skillet for 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes one dozen large muffins.
(Some prefer meal and flour half and half.)

title: turkey-broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in turkey. Spoon mixture over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan and melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry jam
directions: Pick over cranberries; wash. Add raisins.
Peel oranges; remove seeds.
Combine fruits and chop.
Add sugar, salt and water; cook until thick, about 30 minutes, stir often.
Pour into hot sterile jars; store in cool place.

title: doughnut pudding
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Beat 1 quart milk, eggs and salt first and then stir in the doughnuts and mix well.
Next, mix 4 quarts milk, vanilla and cinnamon together and add to the egg-doughnut mixture.
Let stand until the doughnuts are softened.
Bake in pans (9 x 13 x 2-inch) set in hot water in a 350° oven until the doughnut (yeast type) pudding is firm.
Serve a Nutmeg Sauce over the pudding which is served warm.
Sauce recipe is found elsewhere.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: After removing lumps from potatoes, add cream cheese and butter in small pieces. Mix in sour cream. Mix milk, eggs and onions. Add salt and pepper. Beat well. Place in greased casserole; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie pan and bake 35 minutes at 400° in preheated oven.
Makes its own shell.

title: international peas
directions: Boil peas, water, celery and bouillon cubes together for 4 or 5 minutes.
Make a paste of the cornstarch and 1/2 cup of water. Add to hot vegetable mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Just before serving, add sliced water chestnuts and slivered almonds to suit taste.
Serves 6 to 8.
Dee-licious!

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half of crumbs in 9x13 inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth. Mix in confectioner's sugar.
Fold in cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix together pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese mixture into pudding mixture.
Pour in pan on top of crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate to set.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube or loaf pan.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Combine sugar, oil and eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until it tests done.

title: smoked salmon
directions: Mix and put in mold or ball.

title: roasted bologna
directions: Slice bologna in half lengthwise so that it won't wobble in the pan.
Place bologna, cut side down, in a roasting pan. Brush with barbecue sauce.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in large saucepan; boil 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each one.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavorings; beat 1 minute on high speed.
Use greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Test with toothpick.
Cool in pan not inverted.
If you use a Bundt pan, cook part of batter in another pan or it will run over.

title: chocolate gooey bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Sprinkle and pat dry cake mix over butter.
Sprinkle marshmallows, chocolate chips and cereal.
Drizzle milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While warm, run knife around edge.
Cool 2 hours.
Makes 48 bars.

title: praline grahams
directions: Place graham crackers side by side on a 15 x 10-inch greased cookie sheet with raised sides.
Boil butter and sugar together for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread over crackers.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; let settle a few seconds.
Spoon excess on crackers and remove each cracker individually to another cookie sheet to cool. Makes 40 cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix chopped beef and cream cheese together.
Add chopped onions and blades, salt and Worcestershire.
Mix well and roll into a ball.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in flat 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add water and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix butter, flour and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° in conventional oven for 50 minutes or 10 to 12 minutes in microwave.

title: apple stuffing
directions: Melt bacon fat in a skillet.
Add apples and sugar; cook over medium-low heat, stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; toss in the crumbs, nutmeg and cinnamon.
This is a nice alternative for holiday cooking.

title: falafel(the hot dog of the middle east)
directions: Soak chickpeas in water overnight.
Drain; mix drained chickpeas and spices together, then grind very fine.
Add baking soda and let the mixture rest for half an hour.
Form into walnut size balls and deep fry in 350° oil.
Drain well.
May be eaten hot or at room temperature.
Serve with Tahina Sauce (recipe follows) and chopped tomatoes.
Must do ahead, time consuming.
Can freeze.

title: bean soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water and cook until tender. Mash.
Add ham juice and beans.
Bring to temperature and serve.

title: san francisco fudge(quick microwave recipe)
directions: Combine condensed milk, marshmallows and chocolate chips in microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
See chart if microwave is less than 200 watts.
Remove and stir until creamy.
Add vanilla, salt and walnuts; stir.
Place in pan lined with wax paper and refrigerate until hard.
Store at room temperature.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Wash the shrimp with cold water; drain.
Break into chunks. Soften the cream cheese.
Blend in chili sauce and milk; mix well. Stir in shrimp and Worcestershire sauce.
Serve with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: old bean recipe
directions: Soak beans overnight; discard liquid.
Combine beans with other ingredients.
Add water to cover.
Place in roaster or bean pot. Bake for 7 hours at 300°.
Cover during first hour.
Add water frequently to keep beans barely covered.
Cream or 3 tablespoons butter the last drink you give the beans.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix above ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: no cook lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Mix 2 eggs in a bowl.
Add cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and oregano.
Mix egg-cheese mixture well.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Frozen:
Dump strawberries into blender with the powdered sugar and softened butter.
Whirl away until fluffy.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Mix together the zucchini and sugar and let stand overnight. Next morning, add the ground fruit to the squash mixture.
Cook in oven, stirring often until transparent.
Put in jars and seal.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook onions and margarine for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients (mix together these ingredients before adding to onions and margarine).
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Double recipe if using large roast or large amount stew beef.
Cook stew beef or roast in crock-pot.
Remove and cut into bite size pieces.
Put meat into barbecue sauce.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend on medium speed all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool for 15 minutes and spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in bacon slices.
Place slices of dried beef on top of each chicken breast.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve with Stove Top stuffing.

title: dressing for green salad
directions: Measure into jar in order given.
Cover; shake.
Refrigerate and use as needed.

title: freezer sweet corn
directions: Remove corn from cob by cutting off top 1/2 kernels.
Scrape cob lightly to get remaining pulp.
Place corn in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer margarine on top of corn.
Sprinkle sugar over all.
(Add milk if corn is not juicy.) Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Stir thoroughly.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes longer or until bubbly once again.
Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Place in freezer containers.
Seal, label and freeze. Makes about 6 pints.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk. Stir in sugar, salt and melted butter (margarine).
Add flour and beat well.
Let rise until almost double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out on lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thick. Cut in about 2-inch pieces. Dip each piece in melted butter.
Pile in buttered pans (I use tube pan) until half full.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve uncut.
It is already buttered.

title: 4 minute fudge
directions: Put water in a 3-quart Tupperware bowl, 1/4 full.
In a 2-quart Tupperware bowl, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk; stir until mixed well.
Add softened butter; cover with 3/4-quart Tupperware cover.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cover. Microwave 2 more minutes on High.
Add vanilla.
Stir.
Add nuts. Stir.
Spread on pan.
Cool, cut and eat.

title: ozark mountain bean soup
directions: Let simmer together until tender.
If desired, remove fat off bacon pieces.
Good with Mexican cornbread.

title: cinnamon rolls(15 rolls)
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan or muffin pans.

title: swiss vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place vegetables in small, lightly greased, casserole dish.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Stir into vegetables.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes. Place remaining cheese on for the last 5 minutes of baking. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili for 50 people
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Fry hamburger.
Add chili beans, tomato sauce, chili seasoning and tomatoes.
Serves 50 people on a roaster.

title: wonderfully simple roast
directions: Put the frozen roast into a large Dutch oven. Pour the dry onion soup mix over the frozen roast and in the bottom of the pan. Add 1/2 cup water, cover top of pan with foil, then put lid onto pan and bake at 275° for 4 hours or until done. A good roast gravy can be made from the beef broth.

title: mary's sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour three times with soda and salt.
Cream sugar and Crisco
a short time by hand in mixer bowl.
Does not take much creaming.
Put
mixer bowl on mixer and add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each.
Add 1/2 of the flour; mix on low beater. Add sour cream and vanilla and mix.
Add remainder of flour, mixing on low beater well.	Put in greased pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Drop and sprinkle top with sugar. Bake at 350°
about 10 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Add 1/3 cup of mix per cup of hot water.

title: barbara bush's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt onto waxed paper.
Reserve.
Beat together butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl until fluffy. Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in oats and chocolate pieces.
Drop batter by rounded tablespoonful 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer cookies to wire rack to cool.

title: ranch-style potato slices(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat
oven to 400°.
Place potato slices in nonstick 8-inch square
pan.
Pour water over; cover and bake potatoes until tender, but not crumbly (about 40 minutes).
Drain.
Mix dressing and cheese sauce.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with green onion and bacon.
Serve while warm.

title: maryland lady crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix breadcrumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix gently, but thoroughly.
If mixture is too dry, add a little more mayonnaise.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Cook cakes in frypan, in just enough fat to prevent sticking, until browned, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach, using package directions.
Drain; squeeze out excess moisture.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve as a dip with fresh vegetables.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Cook until it coats spoon.
Cool and add 1 package Knox gelatine, 1 quart cream and 1 quart milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to mixture in can.
Add teaspoon vanilla.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: egg strata(this is great for a brunch!)
directions: Put slices of bread in dish.
Cook sausage.
Add mustard and mushrooms.
Sprinkle this over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, pop in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: dinner rolls(basic dough)
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until all is liquid.
Add well beaten egg.
Dissolve dry yeast in the 1/2 cup of lukewarm water.
Add to mixture.
Stir in three cups plain flour.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator at least 20 minutes before kneading and rolling into desired rolls.
You may roll dough and cut with biscuit cutter, spread with melted butter and fold over. Let rise at least 1 hour before baking.
Or you may pinch dough in balls (walnut size), place in muffin tins for Parker House style rolls.
Rolls may be frozen and baked later.
Remove from freezer at least three hours prior to baking.
This dough may be used for coffee rolls or doughnuts.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, milk, garlic salt and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese in food processor; mix well.
Transfer mixture to saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Layer broccoli, half of sauce, chicken and remaining sauce in prepared baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop fine the sweet green peppers, sweet red peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes. Drain and cover again; let come to a boil and allow to stand 10 minutes.
Drain dry and add salt, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook for 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Yields approximately 5 pints.

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour in pan and sprinkle cake mix on top. Put in nuts and spoon melted margarine on top, then sprinkle brown sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla. Add one egg at a time; beat well. Then add dry ingredients. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken curry salad
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add bouillon cubes, spices and flavorings.
Simmer chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from juice and remove skin and bones. When cool, cut into bite size pieces and place in a bowl.
Add the fruit, celery and salad dressing.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries, oranges, celery and nuts and mix it together. Pour sugar over mixture and let stand 2 hours.
Dissolve jello and mix all together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a gallon container, then add water to make 1 gallon.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, add ice ring and ginger ale in a punch bowl.
May change flavors of jello to change taste or color to compliment wedding colors.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix together everything except oil.
Slowly add oil, mixing well.
Pour over chicken or steak and leave overnight (or at least 8 hours).

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mash seasoned squash slightly and mix all ingredients, except stuffing mix together.
Grease casserole and cover bottom with stuffing mix.
Add squash mixture and cover top with remaining buttered stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mama's brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and chocolate syrup. Add flour and blend well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) square greased pans at 350° for 24 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Remove from oven and immediately pour frosting over top.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: nonalcoholic punch
directions: Makes 10 gallons of punch.
Can add champagne.

title: pecan stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems.
Arrange mushroom caps on greased baking sheet.
In skillet, cook chopped mushroom stems, green pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in pecans and remaining ingredients.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon of pecan mixture into each mushroom cap.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together in salad bowl.
Let stand overnight to blend flavors.
Unmold on plate, if desired.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, saving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar, flour and the juice.
Heat over low heat until some of the sugar melts, then stir in pineapple and cheese.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place crushed crackers on top.
Drizzle melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, bananas and milk.
Fold in flour mixture which has been sifted together (flour, baking powder, soda and salt).
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: helen emerton's beef & rice
directions: Saute' onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add flour, cream, salt and pepper; thin with sherry and sour cream.
Add cream cheese and beef.
Add cooked spinach and rice.
Mix all together and put in large casserole.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks, beating well.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in baking dish.
Add salt, pepper, butter and milk.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and butter (margarine) together.
Beat together other ingredients and then add Milky Way mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
(I spray mine with Baker's Joy.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: butterscotch nut fudge
directions: Over low heat cook butter, sugar, brown sugar and sour cream. Stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Beat until luke warm and until it holds shape.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into pan and cool.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of large baking dish.
Bake for about 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: foolproof rice
directions: Rinse rice thoroughly until water is clear.
Then put rice in 2 cups of cold water on stove.

Add butter, salt and lemon juice. Put lid on pot and cook on low heat for 20 minutes (no peeking). Turn off fire and leave lid on pot until ready to serve. Beautiful, flaky rice; no sticking together.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased shallow baking dish, 12 1/4 x 10 1/2-inches.
Cover with crushed Wheaties and dot with dabs of margarine.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until crusty and bubbly.

title: farmers breakfast
directions: In skillet, cook onion and green pepper in margarine until crisp-tender.
Add ham, potatoes and 1/4 teaspoon salt; cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine eggs, 2 tablespoons water, remaining salt and dash of pepper.
Pour over ham mixture.
Cook over low heat, turning occasionally, until eggs are set.
Trim with parsley, if desired.
Serves 6 people.

title: solitaire macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 large baking sheets.
Mix sugar and eggs at high speed.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat until blended.
Beat in butter and vanilla.
Stir in coconut. Drop dough with tablespoon onto baking sheets.
Shape into balls.
Press 1 Solitaire candy into each cookie.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until firm and coconut browns.
Let cool.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in a saucepan over medium heat until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut butter into flour mixture until crumbly.
Firmly press into lightly greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Whisk eggs in large bowl; whisk in 2 cups sugar and lemon juice. Combine remaining 1/4 cup flour and baking powder; whisk into egg mixture. Pour batter over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool completely on wire rack; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Layer on crust.
Bake until golden brown.

title: christine's buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, flour and melted butter.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until custard is set.

title: fruited cheese salad
directions: In mixer bowl, blend together cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Beat until blended.
Stir in dry gelatin.
Fold in pineapple and oranges.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: snappy spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti. Saut garlic in olive oil. When browned, add enough red wine to cover the bottom of you pan and then a little extra. Simmer the garlic in the red wine for a few minutes. Add the spaghetti sauce and oregano. Add the cooked noodles to it. Remove from heat and add chopped green pepper. Stir well, serve with parmesan cheese.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Use an oblong pan or 8 x 12-inch dish.
Spread out cherry pie filling on the bottom of the pan, then spread out the pineapple over the cherry filling.
Sprinkle sugar on top of the pineapple, then put cake mix on top of the sugar.
Spread out margarine gently, then add pecans across the top.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cook 45 minutes or until brown.
It is delicious!

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain, then chop.
Fry bacon.
Add bacon (crumbled), green pepper and onion to squash along with 1 cup of crackers, eggs, salt, pepper and butter.
Mix well and put into baking dish (greased).
Top with remaining cracker crumbs and dot with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Whip Crisco and eggs together.
Add sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts and blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corned beef and cabbage sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes a large bowl.
Keep covered and refrigerated.
Will keep a week or more.

title: veggie bars
directions: *Need 1/2 cup each or whatever.

title: crab cresents
directions: Note: Will last for three months in freezer.

title: chewy date nut strips
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in the eggs.
Stir in dates, nuts and vanilla.
Stir in flour, mixed with the baking powder.
Spoon the batter into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While still warm, cut into strips and roll in granulated sugar.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Form candy mixture around cherries to make small ball.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip candy into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to set.

title: crispy cheese crackers
directions: Mix butter or margarine, cheese and flour until well blended. Add cereal and mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheets.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Add canned vegetables.
Let mixture cook down.
Add pasta.
Mix together.
Add seasonings to taste.
Cook over low heat with lid on pot.
May need to add a little water.

title: american shish kebab(meat and vegetables on a stick)
directions: Clean vegetables and prepare as desired for skewer.
Season vegetables and meat as desired.
Alternately place the meat cubes and vegetables on skewers.
Broil under a hot preheated broiler until the meat is well browned and sizzling.
Remember to rotate the stick!
Serve shish kebab over a rice bed.
May also enjoy sumac and sour cream for extra flavor.

title: chilied chicken fricassee
directions: Combine corn meal, salt, herb mix and pepper in shallow bowl or bag.
Add chicken and coat with mixture.
Heat 3 teaspoons oil in a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven.
Lightly brown chicken on all sides. Remove and set aside.
Add remaining teaspoon of oil to pot. Reduce heat to moderately low and add onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Cook 5 minutes until onion is tender. Add broth and tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add chicken.
Cover pot and cook 25 minutes.
Add corn, peas and beans.
Serve over egg noodles or mix into fricassee.

title: party cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients. Sprinkle wax paper with paprika and roll cheese into a log.
Wrap in foil and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: crock-pot applesauce
directions: Wash and cut apples in chunks.
Put in crock-pot.
Cook on low all day.
Add more sugar if needed.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil. Add seasonings and tomato sauce. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, then add the beans. Pour into a greased baking dish. Spread cornbread batter over meat mixture.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Add water to reserved pineapple liquid to measure 2 cups; bring to a boil in saucepan over medium flame.
Turn off flame.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Blend in cranberry sauce; add ginger ale.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg white; fold in pineapple and celery.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Cover; chill until firm.
Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy; fold in whipped topping.
Frost salad with cream cheese mixture; sprinkle with pecans.
Cover and chill.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Bring to a boil the zucchini and water.
Boil 6 minutes. Add pineapple, lemon juice and sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add apricot jello.
Put in jars.

title: fruit salad
directions: Wash and peel peaches and bananas; slice.
Mix with blueberries and syrup.

title: chicken breasts in mushroom sauce
directions: Combine mushrooms and onions in quart casserole.
Cover; microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until mushrooms are tender. Drain well.
Place butter in 4 cup measure and microwave 30 seconds.
Blend in flour.
Add sherry, water, yogurt, salt and pepper.
Stir in mushrooms and pour over chicken breasts. Microwave 14 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; add peppers and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots.
Stir gently.

title: banana spice cake(this cake will spice up your life.)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and spices together. Add brown sugar, shortening and 1/2 cup milk; beat for 2 minutes. Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Cook squash until done; drain.
Add butter, then mash until smooth.
Add other ingredients. Pour into pie shell and bake until crust is done at 350°.
Add meringue and bake until brown.

title: ratatouille(serves 5 to 6)
directions: Heat oil.
Saute eggplant.
Add zucchini and saute until lightly browned; set aside.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic and salt and pepper.
Saute until onion turns transparent.
Add tomatoes and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add eggplant-zucchini mixture and simmer.

title: ugly cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Melt 1/2 stick butter. Pour in Bundt pan and add pecans. Mix yellow cake mix as directed on box, then pour on top of butter and pecans. Mix cream cheese, 1 stick softened butter and powdered sugar. Spoon this mixture on top of yellow cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool for 5 minutes, then dump it out on a pan. Really good when it is hot.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sour cream and stir until dissolved.
Place in refrigerator.
Chill until mixture gets to the thickness of egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in mold and refrigerate until set.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch dish or pan.
Cut off crusts and cut each piece into 5 fingers.
Place fruit in bottom of pan.
Lay bread fingers over fruit.
Beat together egg, sugar, flour and melted margarine.
Drizzle over bread fingers.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Canned fruit may be used, if drained.
Use about equivalent of fresh fruit.

title: apple bean bake(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Melt butter.
Add cubed apples and cook until tender.
Add brown and white sugars.
Cook until sugars are melted.
Stir in cinnamon, catsup and molasses.
Add beans and mix well.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 400° oven for about 1 hour.

title: polish apple pancakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour batter by 1/2 cupfuls onto a lightly greased, hot griddle or frypan and spread to form a 5-inch circle.
Turn when bubbles form.
Cook on second side until golden brown and apples are tender.
Spread with powdered sugar, if desired. Delicious!

title: impossible blender pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend for 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep baking dish.
Mix other ingredients. Pour over melted margarine.
Add the sliced peaches (juice, too); do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Batter will rise to top during baking and will be crusty when cobbler is done.

title: zucchini-apricot jam
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large pan. Cook 10 minutes. Then add Jell-O and stir well. Place in glass jars and seal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan, at 350° for one hour.
Let cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Thoroughly cool cake before frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain and mash squash.
Mix all ingredients, except margarine and crackers.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef skillet supper
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Add the tomato sauce and water.
Cover and cook for 8 minutes.
Drain the noodles; add to beef mixture. Add corn, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook until heated through and the cheese is melted.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: overnight pecan coffeecake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom and sides of pan.
Space dough balls evenly.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over dough balls.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar; cool.
Pour over dough.
Cover.
Leave overnight (9 to 11 hours).
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn out immediately and serve warm.

title: turkey patties oriental
directions: Mix turkey, bread crumbs, egg and garlic.
Form into 4 to 6 patties, each about 3/4-inch thick.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute burgers 3 minutes on each side, until browned. Mix Oriental Sauce and pour over burgers; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; add celery, onion and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 6 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes until meat is no longer pink.

title: monster chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, cream the butter with an electric mixer.
Beat in the sugar until well combined. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then add the vanilla.
On low speed, blend in the flour mixture, stirring in the last bit with a wooden spoon.
Stir in the chocolate chunks.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry each tomato slice.
Sprinkle cornmeal on a piece of wax paper or large flat surface.
Dip each slice in cornmeal; pat gently until cornmeal covers surface.
Turn over and repeat. Heat vegetable oil in large frying pan over medium heat.
Add tomato slices; fry 2 to 3 minutes on each side until golden brown. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: plantation spoon bread
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Gradually stir in corn meal and cook until thickened.
Add butter, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add hot mixture slowly to eggs, stirring constantly. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in hot oven for 45 minutes.
Serve at once; can be served with butter or gravy.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter, sugar and 3/4 cup lemonade; mix until fluffy. Beat in egg, vanilla and lemon. In separate bowl, stir together flour and baking soda. Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, beating until thoroughly combined. Place the remaining 1/2 cup of lemonade mix in shallow dish. Form dough into 1-inch balls and roll them in lemonade mix, then place them 2-inches apart on a well-greased cookie sheet. Bake cookies until edges just begin to brown, about 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to a rack. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In stockpot, add sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well. Add oats gradually, mixing well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool and serve.

title: gale's lemon rounds(a golden soft cookie)
directions: Bake a butter cake.
Buy one large container of Safeway strawberries.
Buy one large container of Cool Whip.
Poke little holes into the cake with a toothpick.
Pour the strawberries all over the cake and spread them evenly.
Spread the Cool Whip on top of the strawberries, be careful not to let the juice get into the white creme, but if it does, that is okay, the cake is still good either way.
Enjoy!

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients; add oil and mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Stir in pineapple with juice and carrots.
Bake in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch or 3 (7 x 3-inch) loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to batter.
Stir in berries.
Spread batter in lightly greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of pie crust.
Pour filling over bananas.
Cover and chill until set, about 4 hours.
Spread whipped cream on top and garnish with remaining banana slices. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: summer fruit bowl
directions: Combine fruit and orange juice in a large bowl; toss to mix well.
Chill until serving.
To serve, spoon into individual dishes; top each with 2 tablespoons yogurt.

title: tuna-vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring 4 cups water to boil.
Cook macaroni on medium 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt milk and Velveeta together over medium heat and stir in cooked macaroni.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain tuna and Veg-All together in strainer.
Add extra frozen vegetables if desired.
Mix in macaroni and cheese mixture.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour mixture in dish.
Melt butter and stir into crushed crackers. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cook the apples with 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar. Mash and cool. Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat.
Add apples and soda. Sift flour and cinnamon and add. Add fruit that has been dredged with a bit of the flour.
Mix well.
Bake in a moderate oven in a well oiled and paper lined pan for approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Extra nuts and cherries may be added.

title: holiday slush
directions: Add 1 cup sugar and 2 cups water; boil together and cool. Then add orange juice, pineapple juice and bananas.
Freeze. Spoon into glasses and pour 7-Up over it.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put the soup mix, potatoes and oil in a plastic bag.
Shake until potatoes are colored.
Remove from bag; place in a baking dish and cook for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and cooked through.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples	and sugar and let stand for 10 minutes. Mix oil and egg well.
Add apples and other ingredients.
Bake in 8-inch pan	about
minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or frozen topping.

title: sweet dip for fruit
directions: Cream together.
Serve with chunks of fruit (such as:
apples, bananas, pineapple, grapes, strawberries, kiwi fruit, pears, etc.).

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper; pound to 1/8-inch thick or as thin as possible.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place flour on plate; dip chicken in flour to coat both sides, shaking off excess.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add half the chicken and cook each side until golden, about 2 minutes per side.
Transfer to platter.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to skillet and repeat with remaining chicken.
Transfer to platter.
Add chicken broth and lemon slices to skillet, stirring to scrape up browned bits.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon butter. Pour sauce over chicken.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells until tender.
Pour off water and place shells in oblong baking dish.
Stuff with spinach or broccoli.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper and garlic powder.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: congo squares(blonde brownies)
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and mix well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Add chips and nuts.

title: rigatonis
directions: Precook rigatonis for about 5 minutes just until halfway tender.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Mix hamburg, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Take each rigatoni noodle and stuff with hamburg.
Put in pan or dish.
Bake.
Make one layer.
Put layer of cheese, the sauce, another layer, sauce, then cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with garlic bread or rolls.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and white syrup to a full boil.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Mix well, then turn off burner.
Add corn flakes. Pour out in large pan and let cool.
Then roll into small balls and they're ready to eat!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix; do not beat pudding mix and milk.
Then blend in sour cream and Cool Whip.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients. Stir in milk. Add margarine, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 3/4 cups cheese until melted. Add elbows.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with reserved cheese. Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Place chicken breasts, skin side up, in pan.
Spoon mixture over and baste occasionally.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Blend coconut, pecans, milk, margarine and powdered sugar and roll by hand into small balls (about the size of walnuts). Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour but best to chill overnight.

title: sour cream jalapeno corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups or use paper or foil baking cups.
Thoroughly mix corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Beat eggs and sour cream with a whisk or fork in a small bowl.
When smooth, stir in jalapenos.
Pour over mixture.
Fold in with rubber spatula until well mixed; batter will be very stiff.
Scoop batter into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until firm to the touch in the center.
Let cool 5 minutes before turning out onto rack to cool.

title: crab spread or dip
directions: Blend all together and spread over fresh baked bread; broil and sprinkle with paprika.

title: walter's 30 minute homemade pizza
directions: You will need a pizza stone.

title: apple square cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add apples.
When baked, dust with powdered sugar.
Grease and flour a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together butter or margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir in milk or cream and lemon extract.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add potatoes and eggs.
Mix well.
Mix syrup, salt, milk and vanilla.
Add the potato mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Chunk chicken.
Melt down cheese and Ro-Tel.
Add soup and chicken.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: rosa's ice cream
directions: Scald milk. Add slowly to beaten egg yolks. Stir in salt and sugar. Cook over low heat until mixture boils for 1 minute. Stir frequently. Cool. Freeze in the refrigerator tray for 30 minutes. Whip cream until stiff. In another bowl, beat frozen mixture until smooth. Add vanilla. Fold in cream. Pour back into tray. Freeze. Stir often the first hour of freezing. Serves 6.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine egg, sour cream and buttermilk; sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar and add to liquids.
Mix until batter is lumpy, but don't overbeat.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of batter onto hot griddle and cook until bubbles form on top.
Turn and brown the other side.
Makes about 14 pancakes.

title: quick and easy lasagna *
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender.

Brown crumbled beef until it loses its red color, add sauce and oregano. In oblong Pyrex dish about 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch, layer 3 noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and sauce twice, ending with sauce. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Plenty for 5 servings.

title: cheese cocktail appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on rye bread.
Broil until the cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Place defrosted strawberries, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and salt in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat at medium speed for 15 minutes or until mixture is stiff and holds shape.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Clean and cut up chicken.
Stew, when done, cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Put chicken in dish, add cream of celery soup with 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Add peas and carrots to the chicken mixture.
Mix Bisquick with milk and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is brown.
Can be made ahead and pour Bisquick mixture just before cooking.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Combine with corned beef, soup, milk, cheese and onion in a 3-quart casserole.
Top with potato chips. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Stir and pour in baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Mix and add flour, whipping cream, vanilla and lemon flavoring. Flour and grease tube pan. Put in cold oven and bake at 250° until done.

title: mama's blueberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Use mixer to cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg is added.
Add flavorings and beat until fluffy.
Dredge berries with 1/4 cup flour and set aside.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder and salt.
Fold into cake batter until well blended.
Gently stir in berries.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake test done with a cake tester.
Place pan on rack and cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Beat good.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook sausage.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems. Combine with sausage, garlic and parsley.
Stir in cheese and mix well.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine veggies in large bowl.
Sprinkle tacos on top.
Cook ground turkey in nonstick pan until water evaporates.
Add tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour hot turkey-tomato mixture over veggies.
Mix quickly and thoroughly until lettuce is wilted.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Serve warm or cold.
(This is a great low-fat, low calorie meal!)

title: orange sherbet cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and orange juice in large bowl.
Stir in coconut.
Reserve 1 cup whipped topping.
Fold remaining whipped topping into sour cream mixture.
Chill for 24 hours.
Combine cake mix, gelatin, eggs, oil and water in mixer bowl; beat well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until layers test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Split layers into halves horizontally.
Reserve 1 cup icing.
Spread remaining icing between layers.
Mix reserved whipped topping and reserved icing in bowl.
Spread over top of cake.
Chill in airtight container in refrigerator for 1 to 2 days. Yield:
12 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips at medium speed for about 5 minutes. Add chips and stir.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: cheesecake
directions: Chill Milnot overnight.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Spread in deep dish.
Mix jello with one cup boiling water, then chill until a syrup stage.
Watch closely.
Cream the cream cheese and one cup sugar with the vanilla; add jello and mix.

title: southern style beans
directions: Place beans in an oven-ready pan and add barbecue sauce, green pepper and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add brown sugar and bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate surprise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°; grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix, water, oil and eggs until moist; beat 2 minutes on high.
Spoon cake mixture over nut mixture in pan.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add by 1/2 cup to batter, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 12 minutes.

title: spicy breakfast rice pizza
directions: In a 2 or 3-quart saucepan, combine rice, water, salt and butter or margarine. Bring to a boil. Stir once or twice. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove pan from heat. Uncover and fluff rice with a fork. While rice is cooking, brown and drain the sausage. Spread crescent roll dough evenly onto pizza pan. Beat eggs and mix with the Ro-Tel tomatoes, pepper and paprika. Combine egg mixture with cooked rice and sausage. Spread evenly over the dough. Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: favorite wild rice
directions: Wash and soak wild rice overnight.
Cook until tender.
Cook white rice.
Saute celery and onion, brown hamburger.
Combine all ingredients in covered casserole or Dutch oven.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: You will need 1 medium saucepan and 1 strainer.

title: bev's delicious salad dressing
directions: Shake well to mix.
Refrigerate.
So easy and so good!

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork; mix cornstarch, soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger, vinegar and water.
Pour over browned pork and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add pineapple, onion and green pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serve pork sauce over hot rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put melted margarine in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Pour peaches over margarine.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Add to dish and stir slightly.
Bake at 350° until brown and thick.

title: mami elva's fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit cocktail, pears, cherries, apples, banana, walnuts and coconut.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme.
If too thick add some reserve fruit juice.
Mix well; chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: date balls
directions: Using the chopped, sugar-rolled package of dates makes this quick and easy.

title: plank cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in order listed.
Then sift and mix as much flour as you require to make a dough that can be molded by the hands into flat "planks" about 6-inches long and 3-inches wide, about 1/2-inch thick.
Set on greased pans 2-inches apart so when they spread, they will not touch one another.
Bake in slow oven and look at them often, as anything that contains molasses is apt to burn quickly.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Toss butter with bread crumbs.
Arrange 1/3 of crumbs on bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with half of apples and half of combined sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cover with 1/3 of crumbs, rest of apples and rest of sugar mixture.
Spoon on combined lemon juice and water.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake covered for 1/2 hour.
Uncover, bake for 1/2 hour more or until apples are done.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, water and vanilla. Beat on medium speed until blended.
Beat eggs into mixture. Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips by hand. Drop by spoonfuls of cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 7 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook onions and garlic in skillet for 5 minutes.
Add ground chuck; cook, stirring occasionally until meat loses its red color. Add salt, pepper and tomatoes. Simmer covered for 30 minutes, then discard garlic.
Add chile powder and water.
Bread half of uncooked spaghetti into greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour on half of sauce.
Sprinkle with half of cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, 35 minutes at 350°; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning in bottom of a rectangular baking pan. Spread salsa over.
Spread tomatoes. Spread onion, then lettuce, then cheese.
Chill. Serve as a dip with nacho chips. Great to take to a barbecue or party.

title: hot cocktail canapes
directions: Mix all together.
Mound on about 40 bite size cuts of a variety of breads and broil until puffed and browned (about 2 minutes).

title: easy chicken stew
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Heat until hot and bubbly. Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each in half. Drop biscuit halves into hot chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley. Cook over medium heat, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Cover tightly and simmer 15 minutes longer. Serve immediately. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: barbecue drummettes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except pineapple and chicken.
Place drummettes in single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Pour barbecue mixture over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until drummettes are not pink inside.

title: hot and sour barbecue chicken
directions: Chop the onion and saute it in the margarine until the onion is clear.
Add the vinegar, lemon juice and the remains of half a squeezed lemon.
Pour in the Worcestershire sauce and 2 or 3 drops of Tabasco.
Sprinkle in the peppers and cumin to taste.
(Start with very little, then add more as needed.)
Simmer for about half an hour, then add more of the peppers, if necessary.
Place the chicken on a hot grill and spoon or mop some sauce on each piece. Cook slowly, putting more sauce on the chicken each time it is turned.
Remove cooked chicken from the grill and serve.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Crush wafers in plastic bag.
Melt butter or margarine and combine with crumbs.
Press evenly into 8-inch pie plate or the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill well before filling.

title: fantastic ambrosia
directions: Toss banana slices in orange juice, drain; reserve juice. Layer the orange sections, bananas and strawberries. Cover and chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil and sugar and mix well by hand.
Add zucchini and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to batter.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake 40 to 55 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook noodles until tender; drain. Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise or salad dressing, celery, onion, pepper, pimento (if using) and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Clean chicken parts thoroughly.
Place in kettle with water and simmer one hour or more, adding more water if necessary.
Add vegetables and simmer for another hour.
Remove chicken parts and set aside.
Allow broth to cool.
Then remove fat.
Strain through cheese cloth placed in a strainer.
Discard vegetables.
Remove skin and bones from cooked chicken.
Separate meat into chunks.

title: muscadine jelly
directions: Boil muscadines until soft; strain in colandar.
Separate juice from pulp.
Add 1 pound sugar to one pint of juice.
Boil until it congeals when dropped in a cup of ice water.
It takes about 30 minutes or more.
Watch closely.
May stir slightly.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: veal with dill
