directions: Saute veal in 4 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add garlic, onion and 2 tablespoons of the dill.
Cook without browning for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and nutmeg and add chicken broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour at 375°.
Scrape carrots and trim leeks.
Split leeks down center and rinse well.
Slice carrots and leeks lengthwise into very thin strips.
Set aside.
Heat 4 tablespoons of butter and cook leeks and carrots until wilted.
Stir 1/2 vegetables into meat.
Stir in cream and bring to a boil.
Use remaining vegetables to garnish when served over noodles or rice.

title: bean bake
directions: Cook and drain hamburger and onion.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Drain beans to suit you.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread, onion, baking powder, egg, 3 tablespoons catsup, 1/2 tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Make into loaf and place 3 strips of bacon on top of loaf.
Pour rest of tomatoes, rest of catsup and one can of water over loaf to make gravy.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix melted margarine, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in flour, salt and nuts.
Roll into small balls and bake in 400° oven until firm; don't let them get brown.
Roll immediately in powdered sugar.
Roll again.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and pecans.
Roll into balls.
Place on a tray and put in freezer for about 2 to 3 hours.
Take out of freezer and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook for 20 to 24 minutes at 325°. Cool lightly.
Dip in powdered sugar about 3 to 4 times each.

title: clam sauce
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet on low heat.
Stir in flour and garlic salt with wire whisk.
Add liquid from clams.
Continue to stir.
Add seasonings.
Add clams last.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Good over cooked, thin spaghetti.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: uncle laine's quiche(it's easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Glass pans work best.
Should be about 1 to 1 1/2-inches deep, any shape will do.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Put in microwave oven for 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir twice while cooking.
Very good served on ham.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat, onion and bell pepper together. Drain. Mix in bowl all other ingredients.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Scald the
milk
and add sugar, oleo and salt.	Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve
the yeast in warm water.
Add to the milk mixture.
Add the eggs and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth and add the rest of the flour, to make a soft dough.
Place in a greased
bowl, cover and let rise.	Punch the dough down and let rise
again.
Divide
in
3 parts.	Roll each in a 12-inch circle and
cut
in 16 wedges.
Brush with extra butter.
Roll tightly from wide end to point.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: pine nut and orange fudge
directions: Line 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil, overlapping sides.
Combine all ingredients except pine nuts in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium to low heat until sugar dissolves, about 15 minutes. Brush down sugar crystals from sides of pan, using wet pastry brush.
Increase heat to high and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium-high and cook until candy thermometer registers 234°, stirring frequently, about 12 minutes.
Pour mixture onto rimmed cookie sheet; do not scrape pan.
Let mixture cool for 15 minutes. Scrape mixture into medium metal bowl using rubber spatula.
Using electric mixer, beat until fudge is thick and creamy and no longer glossy, about 5 minutes.
(To test fudge for proper consistency, mound fudge mixture on spoon and turn upside down.
If mixture falls off spoon, beat fudge again and repeat test.)
Mix in pine nuts and immediately transfer fudge to prepared pan.
Cover with plastic and press to flatten fudge into even layer.
Refrigerate until firm enough to cut, about 1 hour.
Lift fudge from pan, using foil as aid.
Fold foil sides down.
Trim ends of fudge.
Cut into pieces.

title: chicken with spanish sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Heat oil in heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken pieces and brown them quickly.
Remove chicken pieces to a casserole and add black pepper.
Set aside.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add chicken.
Thoroughly coat.
Place chicken in baking pan and pour remaining sauce on. Cook, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven for the first hour and 400° for the last half hour.
Turn chicken after 45 minutes.

title: chuck wagon steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and rub into meat, both sides.
Heat oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat on all sides. Blend broth, water, BBQ sauce and chili powder.
Pour over meat; cover and cook 1 hour.
Add green peppers and olives.
Simmer 1 - 1 1/2 hours longer.
Great served over rice or with mashed potatoes.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Dip each piece in butter; roll in crumbs.
Place skin side up in casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour remaining butter around chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: seasoned onion potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Put in a container with a lid. Pour oil over potatoes; add soup mix.
Put lid on and shake well until evenly coated.
Lay potatoes in a pan or on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form a ball.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on high 4 to 6 hours.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Dredge one side of each bacon strip in cheese.
Roll it, cheese side in, diagonally around a bread stick.
Place on paper towel-lined platter.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Roll again in cheese.

title: french bread french toast
directions: In food processor, chop peaches coarsely.
Add jam; process briefly.
In shallow dish, beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Slice bread in 1/2-inch slices diagonally.
Soak bread in egg mixture thoroughly.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and pour into 11 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Slice butter over the top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whip cream.

title: leatherbocks(very spicy cookies)
directions: Heat molasses to lukewarm; add brown sugar, vinegar and egg. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Add to molasses mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful on cookie sheet, leaving room to spread.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: south carolina pound cake
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients and add sugar.
Beat until fluffy, approximately 10 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one until the yellow disappears.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Mix on low speed, scraping the sides of the bowl. Do not overbeat.
Add extract and oil; stir until well blended. Pour mixture into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Place cake in a cold oven and bake it at 300° until golden brown and an inserted toothpick comes out clean (approximately 1 1/2 hours). Allow cake to settle and cool before removing from pan.

title: coleslaw
directions: Toss ingredients together. Add mayonnaise and blend well. Serve cold.

title: turkey-vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Put all in a bowl and beat until thick.

title: dill beans
directions: Use green or wax beans.
Remove tips, stems and strings from beans.
Wash and drain.
Combine water, salt and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Pack beans in freshly sterilized jars.
Add several sprays of dill.
Fill jars with boiling brine.
Cook 5 minutes and seal.
Let stand a week before using.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover each piece with a cheese slice.
Combine soup and wine.
Pour over chicken. Crush enough croutons to cover top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: red wine biscotti(serve with cream cheese caviar spread)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in food processor and process only until combined.
Do not overmix. Remove dough and divide into thirds.
Divide each third into eighths.
Roll each piece into 3-inch lengths and form into a donut shape.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 24 biscotti.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Pound salt, pepper and flour into steak on both sides.
Brown meat in shortening.
Layer onions, green pepper and celery on top of meat.
Cut tomatoes and add on top of vegetables.
Add tomato juice.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce on top of tomatoes.
Cover and cook on low heat until meat is tender.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.

title: beef noodle soup
directions: Cut stew beef into bite-size pieces; brown well in butter. Cover with water.
Add chopped ingredients, minced garlic, parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender.
Add rice and allow to cook.
When tender, add a small amount of egg noodles.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil, strain and cool
macaroni.
Chop green peppers and onions.
To cool macaroni, add mustard and 1/2 bottle of dressing. Add green peppers, onions and chicken.
Add the rest of the dressing; use second bottle, if desired.
Spread cheese on top and chill.
Add more dressing and cheese for individual servings, if desired.

title: saw dust salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and orange gelatin in 2 cups hot water. Add cold water, crushed pineapple, diced bananas and miniature marshmallows. Chill in refrigerator until congealed.

Then	cook until thickened, sugar, egg, pineapple and flour. Allow to cool, spread this mixture over congealed gelatin. Mix cream cheese and cool whip, beat until light. Spread over second layer. Sprinkle grated sharp cheese over top.

title: molasses drop cakes
directions: Mix sugar and spices; add oil, molasses plus well beaten egg. Stir in sifted flour, salt and soda.
Add boiling water.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream topping with shaved crystallized ginger.
Makes 8 to 9 large cupcakes.

title: chile sauce
directions: Boil in uncovered kettle for several hours, stirring occasionally.
Can.
Makes about eight 1/2-quart jars.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Cook oleo, dates, sugar and eggs together.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well and form into small strawberry shapes.
Roll in red sugar.

title: mock chicken divan
directions: Place deboned chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soup with milk. Pour over chicken.
Cook for about an hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: dad's jello
directions: Blend Jell-O, cream cheese and water in blender until cream cheese is mixed.
Add pineapple (drained).
Add 1 cup cold water. Stir.
Pour in mold or bowl.
Refrigerate until starts to jell and add Cool Whip.

title: 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: rainwater chili
directions: Heat the oil in a large pot over medium high heat.
Add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Stir in the jalapenos, bell peppers and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes longer.
Remove from the heat.
Brown the sirloin and sausage in a skillet, crumbling the meat with the back of a wooden spoon, over medium-high heat just until the meat is no longer pink.
Add the meat to the onion mixture and return the pan to medium heat.
Stir in the tomatoes, tequila, beer and olives.
Season to taste with salt.
Simmer the chili, uncovered, over low heat for about 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine and put in oven at 350°.
Bake until juice cooks down.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Rinse with cold water until cool. Cut up vegetables in large bowl.
Add cold spaghetti; mix together.
Add salad seasoning; mix well.
Pour in dressing.
Stir until all is mixed.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake and pudding according to directions on box. Place cake into a large container.
Crumble it up into fairly large pieces.
Pour pudding over the cake.
Next, spread whipped topping over mixture.
Finally, sprinkle top with Heath Sensations.
This is a large recipe, so it's great for parties!

title: chicken dressing
directions: Pour broth into crock-pot.
Add bread crumbs and remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to low for 1 hour longer.
Stir often and may need to add more broth.

title: acini de pepe macaroni salad
directions: Boil acini de pepe macaroni in salted water; blanch and cool. Combine sugar, flour, salt, pineapple juice and egg yolks together; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Let cool and add macaroni.
Let set in refrigerator overnight. Add mandarin oranges, crushed pineapple, small marshmallows and Cool Whip to previous mixture and chill.

title: better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to a large bowl; cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, mustard, salt and tomato to chilled rice.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple slices
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm milk; set aside.
Sift flour, then measure.
Add butter and mix as for pie crust.
Add yeast and milk mixture and eggs; mix well.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll one part to fit a 12 x 18-inch sheet pan, then spread cooled filling over dough.
Roll remaining dough to fit over the top.
Let rise until light, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Frost with thin frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts or coconut.

title: joanne's potluck salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Boil this liquid, then take from heat and dissolve Jell-O into it.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Place in fridge until slightly thickened. Add pineapple, carrots and nuts and fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef in large skillet.
Cut Velveeta into small slices and lay on top.
Cover until cheese melts.
Add spices.
Mix thoroughly until gooey.
Don't drain grease.
Spoon mixture (stirring frequently) onto rye bread.
I line the bread up on a cookie sheet (easier to handle).
Place, uncovered, in freezer until firm.
Remove from sheet and put in plastic Baggies. Bake for 15 minutes at 350° when needed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Pull off bones and cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients except corn flakes.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes in Pyrex dish.

title: lima bean bake
directions: Wash beans and drain.
Put in pot; cover with water and the ground ginger.
Cook slowly until soft when you pierce with fork. Add more water if necessary.
Dice the salt pork into small squares and saute until lightly browned.
Add 1 large onion (diced) and cook until soft.
Add a small amount of bean water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Put all ingredients into casserole dish; stir to distribute salt pork and onion.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until light brown on top.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
May add 3/4 cup nuts if you wish.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° in muffin pan.

title: mystery dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with cooking spray.
Mix brown sugar, eggs, pecans, flour and baking soda.
Batter will be thick.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.
Whip cream in large bowl.
Fold in brandy.
Break cake into small pieces and fold into cream mixture.
Spoon mixture into clean 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly.
Freeze for 4 hours or overnight.
Spoon into goblets.
Serve from freezer.
Do not let it thaw.

title: tomato soup cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add tomato soup and nuts last.
Grease cupcake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 36 cupcakes.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Stir until dissolved, then add milk.
Stir in pecans.
Butter waxed paper and drop candy onto paper.
Let cool.
Melt morsels and paraffin.
Dip caramel and pecan mixture in chocolate.
Then put back onto waxed paper.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.
Mix sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add 3 eggs and then 1 cup of flour.
Add 3 eggs and then 1 cup of flour until smooth.
Last add lemon extract.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan that has been buttered and lightly floured.
Cook for 1 hour in a preheated 300° oven.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat sugar, eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
Add margarine and blend well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: california salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine with coconut and sour cream.
Chill for 12 hours.
Serve with baked ham.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: reunion punch
directions: In a punch bowl combine punch, cranberry juice and orange juice; blend well. Add ice cubes, lemon slices and lemon soda. Makes 4 3/4 quarts or enough for 38 (4 oz.) servings.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add Mountain Dew and juice from pineapple.
Chill until it thickens.
Cook pudding as directed; cool.
Mix gelatin, lemon pudding and Cool Whip.
Beat together.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.

title: 3 layer jam cake
directions: Cream the butter. Gradually add sugar and cream until light and
fluffy. Add well beaten eggs. Sift flour and add spices and a pinch of salt. Sift again.
Add soda to buttermilk. Alternate ingredients, flour and liquid, ending with flour.
Mix in fruit and nuts.
Add jam last. Grease pans. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.
Especially good with ham instead of potatoes.

title: bee's broccoli salad
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour the dressing over the salad and mix well. Serve chilled.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apples, and mix for 2 minutes. Put on apples and let stand 30 minutes.
Pack in quart jars and seal.
Cook in water bath for 50 minutes.

title: mexican thing
directions: In blender, chop peppers, onions and black olives until fine. Add cream cheese, mayonnaise and garlic salt.
Blend until smooth. Layer mixture between 2 tortillas.
Stack between wax paper. Chill before serving.
Cut rounds like a pizza.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese; add pimento, sugar and salt to taste.
Add mayonnaise by the tablespoonful until you get a desired consistency.

title: no muss - no fuss chocolate cake
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch square pan, greased and floured, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix and sift first 4 ingredients.
Combine sugar and oil.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add all dry ingredients at one time and blend well.
Shape dough in 3/4-inch balls - dip in sugar - place on greased cookie sheet and press.
Bake in 375° oven till done.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with whole graham crackers.
Beat 2 packages of instant pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Add Cool Whip to pudding.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Pour rest of pudding mixture over crackers.
Top with more crackers. Beat chocolate, powdered sugar, Karo, milk and vanilla until mixed well.
Pour over top layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 12 hours before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Toast oats in large, shallow pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: favorite holiday punch
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Before serving add 2 quarts of ginger ale.
Yields 2 1/2 gallons of punch.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
When ready to use, add 3 teaspoons of mix per 1 cup of hot water.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine corn, eggs, corn muffin mix, green chilies and 1/2 cup cheese in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 10 x 10-inch baking dish; sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: mexican chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Do not drain.
In large skillet, melt 1 stick margarine.
Add chili mix, onion, celery and pepper and saute.
Add soup, tomatoes and green chiles.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir until it melts.
Pour this over the spaghetti and add chicken.
Stir.
Put in large casserole and heat 45 minutes at 300°.

title: squash-cheese casserole
directions: Heat milk and pour over bread crumbs.
Add eggs, pepper, butter, onions, squash and cheese.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in 3 quarts boiling water; add 1 tablespoon salt (optional).
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix macaroni, soups, milk, 1 cup cheese and onion together.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Keep covered until last 10 minutes.
Don't hesitate to use extra cheese.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine until creamed.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans when batter has been thoroughly stirred.
Grease 9x9x2-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan and spread.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Wash the cauliflower, break into flowerets.
Combine cauliflower and next 3 ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Toss gently.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables; stir well.
Spoon into serving bowl. Cover and chill before serving.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: petal patch beans
directions: Rinse beans well and place into crock-pot or stove top pot. Add other ingredients.
Cook all day or until done.
(These are especially good the longer you cook them, and even better if cooked one day and eaten the next!)
Serve with fried or mashed potatoes or rice.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core stem out of cabbage.
Place in a large pot of boiling water to wilt leaves.
Mix all ingredients except cabbage in a large mixing bowl.
Puree tomatoes; add 1/2 to meat mixture. Reserve other half to pour over rolls in casserole.
Peel leaves off cabbage.
Roll beef mixture in leaves and place in casserole. Pour remaining pureed tomatoes over rolled leaves.
Cut remaining cabbage and steam in water; drain.
Pour over cabbage rolls, cover casserole and cook on slow to medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until well done.
Add liquid as needed.

title: rice dressing
directions: Cook chicken livers and giblets in cooking oil in Dutch oven and let it brown well.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook slowly. Add chicken broth; stir.
Add parsley, green onions and oysters. Season to taste.
Add rice to make the dressing.
Serve hot.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter or margarine. Gradually add sugar; cream well.
Gradually add cake flour; mix well.
Add flavorings.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Pour into large tube or Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all and put in the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: janet's hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in large baking dish. Top with corn flakes.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over corn flakes.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.
This can be frozen.
If frozen, leave topping off until thawed.

title: california chocolate brownies
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Gradually beat in corn syrup until thoroughly mixed and light and fluffy.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/4 cup at a time to creamed mixture. Fold in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 30 to 35 minutes or until slight imprint remains when touched lightly with finger.
Set pan on rack to cool completely, then sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: cream corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients on medium to low heat 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine flour to the melted butter and add this to the corn mix.
Simmer and stir 5 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar gradually.
Fold in chocolate bits, coloring and extract. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven, with door closed, overnight.
Enjoy.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Pour corn into greased casserole dish.
Crush crackers into corn.
Fill corn can with milk and add to cracker mixture.
Stir well.
Dot top with dabs of butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cake with fruit sauce
directions: Slice cake, top with fruit and Cool Whip.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Cream margarine
and
sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Fold
in	nuts
and
cherries.
Pour into greased 12-inch Dutch oven.
Bake
with
10 coals on top and 8 coals on bottom
for
minutes.	Cool for 10 minutes before trying to remove from oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well;
pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle dressing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill for 1 hour. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: In a skillet brown ground beef and onion; drain and set aside. In a mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, oregano, salt and pepper; beat in eggs.
Stir in beef mixture and 1 cup cheese. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Make cake batter as directed. Fill each cone about 1/2 full. Stand cones in muffin pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool, then frost.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Cream lemon juice, sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Add oil and soy sauce in a small bowl.
Cut venison steaks into cubes.
Put in bowl with salt and pepper to taste.
Let stand 1/2 to 1 hour.
Drain off excess oil and soy sauce.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to a deep frying pan or wok.
Turn on high.
Brown meat.
Take meat out of pan and add vegetables.
Stir-fry until slightly tender, then add meat back and warm a minute longer. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: beans and burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 13 inch x 9 inch baking dish.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix water and margarine in bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, peppers, half of pineapple and syrup.
Spoon stuffing over chicken.
Roll tightly.
Place in a pan.
Mix together remaining pineapple, sugar, vinegar and ginger.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: sausage and spinach casserole
directions: Melt butter and flour together, stirring constantly.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Continue
stirring and cook until thickened. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Put into buttered casserole and top with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300°. (In my oven it takes about 45 minutes at 325°.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Cook slowly.
Then soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Let chill.
Add egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: corn pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in buttered casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
If toothpick dry, it is cooked.
In microwave on High, 17 minutes or less.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes for 45 minutes before assembling.
Combine potatoes in 3-quart (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking dish.
Combine butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese with potatoes. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a large bowl for 3 1/2 minutes in the microwave (stir after 2 minutes). Add cereal, peanuts and raisins to melted mixture.
Stir lightly (do not break Crispix).

title: zippy mexican salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, chili sauce, vinegar, onion salt, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Add cooled, cooked pasta and remaining ingredients; blend well.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: kyoto house dressing
directions: Mix together and shake.
Serve on green salad.
Makes 1/3 cup dressing.

title: gumbo
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet and add flour.
Stir over medium heat until caramel color.
This mixture is called "roux."
Set this aside.
Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add gumbo seasoning and okra.
Cook 3 minutes.
In large pot, combine roux and vegetables.
Stir in chicken broth, sausage and tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Before serving, stir in shrimp and chicken.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve in bowls; garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili
directions: Cook beans until tender; drain broth and save.
Cook meat, onion and bell peppers together.
Drain well and add to beans. Add tomatoes, chopped up.
Add black bean broth until it covers mixture.
Add spices.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Freezes well.
Serve with cornbread.

title: fig newton rolls
directions: Cut each cookie lengthwise into 3 pieces. Roll each piece into confectioners sugar until completely coated.

title: french toast
directions: Preheat griddle to 325° or frypan over medium heat.
Melt butter on griddle or frypan.
Crack egg in bowl.
Mix egg, milk and cinnamon in bowl.
Dip each slice of bread into egg and milk mixture, coating both sides.
Put each piece on hot griddle, turning when bottom is brown and somewhat crisp.
Continue cooking until other side is done.
Remove from pan with turner and put on serving plates.
Top with fruit, jam, maple syrup or honey.
Makes 4 pieces.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, brown sugar, salt and milk; bring to a boil.
Add caramel syrup.
Gradually cook until mixture thickens. Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in colander.
Let stand until thawed and excess water has drained.
Combine sour cream and margarine; mix well. Add salt, onion, cheese and chicken soup; mix well.
Blend in potatoes.
Place in shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered cornflakes on top.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin pans with paper liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in each cup.
Beat cream cheese with mixer until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Spoon mixture into liner filling, 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Can be frozen.
Thaw 5 minutes and add topping.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling, fresh fruit or 3/4 cup sour cream, mixed with 1/4 cup sugar.

title: pecan squares
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and mix all ingredients together. Bake in square pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 dozen.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cube and cook
zucchini in salt water until tender.
Brown onion and carrots in small amount (2 tablespoons) of oleo.
Add mushroom soup and sour cream.
Fold
in
zucchini
and
bread cubes.
Bake
30 to 40 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: banana sour cream mold
directions: Prepare jello per box directions.
Chill until set (thickened).
Add banana slices, sour cream and nuts.
Spoon into mold and let set for at least 4 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices; add with milk.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: a shaker perch chowder, ca 1860
directions: Cut 1 and 1/2 pounds of fish into 2-inch strips.
Cover with sherry and let stand for 30 minutes.
Cut remaining fish in pieces, put in kettle with water to cover.
Add thyme, cloves, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes and cook vegetables in the fish broth until tender.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Add wafers, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and nuts to melted margarine.
Mix well.
Roll into balls about size of walnut.
Melt chocolate chips and wax together.
With a toothpick, pick up balls and dip in chocolate mixture.
Set on wax paper. Makes about 60.
These are also excellent if kept in freezer.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs. Set aside.
Combine last 3 ingredients into large skillet and bring to a boil.
Add meatballs to skillet.
Cover and simmer on low for approximately 1 hour, basting regularly.
Kids love these. Especially if served with macaroni and cheese.

title: polish kluski
directions: Drain; squeeze the grated potatoes.
Add the egg and flour. Form into small balls or drop from a tablespoon into a pot of salted boiling water.
Cook until they float.
With a slotted spoon, transfer to a hot platter.
Saute onion in butter.
Pour over the Kluski.

title: aunt marie's fruit tortillas
directions: Heat until dissolved the water, sugar and margarine.
Fill each tortilla with 1 or 2 tablespoons filling.
Roll up and place seam side down in large oblong baking dish.
Pour syrup (above) over tortillas and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Easy, fast and good.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple with juice. Stir in apples, nuts and marshmallows. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: cheese filled pastry slices
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, juice and egg yolk.
Mix until smooth.
With rolling pin, flatten 1 package of rolls, pinching to close any seams.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with rolled pastry.
Pour in cream cheese mixture and smooth over crust.
Roll out remaining dough, fold into fourths and lift and unfold over cheese mixture.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Spread over top crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil if it browns too quickly.
Remove when done and cool. Sprinkle with sugar; cut in slices or squares.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries; drain, then put through food chopper along with apples and oranges.
Add sugar and chill.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil the sugar, milk and margarine for 6 minutes. Then add the marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla. Mix rapidly. Spread on cake.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: In vegetable steamer, steam the broccoli until just tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
In large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, warm the margarine until melted.
Add the onion, celery and garlic and cook until the onion begins to brown, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove the skillet from the heat.
Add the broccoli, lemon juice, lemon zest, salt and pepper to the skillet and stir to combine.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 8.

title: tomatoes with stale biscuits
directions: Bring tomatoes or juice to boil.
Add soda and salt.
Keep boiling.
Add thickening made of 2 level tablespoons of cornstarch and enough milk to make a smooth paste to which add 3 tablespoons of the hot tomatoes.
Add this to boiling tomatoes, along with the Longhorn cheese and oleo.
Gently stir in either the biscuits or bread, broken into pieces.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent from scorching. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Cool.

title: baked quail
directions: Pan-fry quail until brown.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over fowl.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.
Serve with wild or white rice.

title: pic picking cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until oranges are in tiny pieces. Divide into 3 layers.
Bake at 350° until done.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple in large bowl and spoon over layers.

title: pasta with artichokes and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Soak tomatoes in 1 cup boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain tomatoes, reserve water.
Cut tomatoes into thin strips.
Cook artichoke hearts according to package directions.
Drain well and cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Heat oil in a nonstick skillet and cook onions, garlic and mushrooms 3 minutes.
Add artichokes, tomatoes, tomato liquid and pine nuts.
Cook 3 minutes over medium-low heat. Combine cooked pasta and vegetables.
Toss lightly and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 2 to 3 large servings.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Prepare cake mix substituting pineapple juice for water (add water if necessary). Once cake has cooled, spread pineapple over the top.
Soften the cream cheese.
Beat cream cheese adding 1 1/2 cups milk.
Add pudding mix.
Once it thickens, spread over the cake.
Once it is firm, spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle coconut.
Chill overnight.
Can use 9 x 13-inch pan or prepared as a layer cake. Must be refrigerated.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange rolls in a greased 10 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Cook butter and remaining ingredients over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture bubbles.
Pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil and let stand overnight on counter.
Bake next morning at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: southern spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, cream the sugar with melted butter.
Add egg and yeast mixture. Stir in flour until well mixed.
Place dough in airtight container, filling not more than 2/3 full.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before baking.
Drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: six hour stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a large roaster.
Cover and place in a preheated 250° oven for 6 hours.

title: winter warming vegetable soup
directions: Put shin bone(s) in a large soup pot filled 3/4 full with water.
Add 2 carrots, 2 parsnips, 2 celery stalks and salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil, then simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove shin bones and vegetables from stock.
Add sliced carrots, parsnips, celery, tomatoes and bay leaf to stock and simmer until vegetables are cooked, about 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves. Break meat off the shin bones and add to soup.
Add other assorted vegetables as desired.
Add soup macaroni and continue to simmer as desired.
It is even better the next day.
Serve with fresh crusty Italian or French bread.
